title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: onions a l'ail (stuffed onions)
directions: Hollow out onions.
Make stock.
In pan, brown onion flesh with garlic and margarine.
Add Maggi and water.
Add celery; simmer.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Mix together the beer, oil, lime juice, onion, pepper flakes, cumin and pepper; this is your marinade.

title: mom's quick coffee cake(sunday morning coffee cake)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put the butter in a 9-inch pan and put in the oven only long enough to melt butter.
Mix sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk in several additions.
Add melted butter and stir.
Spread into baking pan. Top with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato-onion piquante
directions: Make several crosswise slices in each potato, not cutting quite all the way through bottom peel (each slice to be approximately 1/2 inch thickness).
Gently open cuts and place one onion slice in each.
Place in a shallow dish.
Cover and bake at 450° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Dot with margarine.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole.
Combine corn, milk and melted butter. Thoroughly blend in bread or cracker crumbs, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish and dot with 2 teaspoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peppers in oil
directions: Make a solution of 3 parts vinegar and one part water; mix cold.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind the first four ingredients.
Add sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Seal in sterile jars.
Yields approximately 5 pints.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Roll bread dough into 14-inch circle.
Layer broccoli, pepperoni and cheeses in order given in center of dough.
Pull edges of dough toward the center; pinch to seal.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 10 servings.

title: impossible broccoli pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese and the onion in the pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate over broccoli.
Bake at 400° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake further until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and add to eggs.
Put in casserole.
Fold in sliced eggs. Top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and melt in small pan.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust according to package.
Press in bottom of spring-form pan (9-inch).

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add bananas, egg yolks and vanilla (beat well).
(Dissolve soda in buttermilk separate.)
Add flour and buttermilk.
Add pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool and ice with Caramel 7-Minute Frosting.

title: deborah rohlack's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix in blender until powder.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated chocolate and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Layer 1: Mix 1 cup flour, 1 stick butter and 1 cup chopped pecans together well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Don't brown. Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and cheese in microwave.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: nutty pasta
directions: Heat spaghetti according to label directions.
Add the peanuts and serve with a salad and garlic toast.

title: sugar glazed walnuts(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, place butter.
Microwave at High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar and microwave at High 2 minutes.
Mix well to combine butter and sugar.
Add nuts and mix well to coat.
Microwave at High 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread out onto wax paper and cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 1 pound.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage; drain.
Peel tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Rinse beans, crumble bacon.
Chop onions and peppers; mince garlic.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook overnight.
Or, may be simmered on the stove.

title: apple date drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg.
Add 1 cup applesauce.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts. Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Yields 6 or 7 dozen cookies.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix Bisquick, beer, salt and pepper.
Dip fillets in mixture and fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Wash raisins; soak for 20 minutes.
Mix flour with liquid from ham.
Add pineapple juice.
Add raisins and water.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add the egg yolks and mix.
Sift the flour and soda.
Mix and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 8 or 9-inch cake pans in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Wash beets and leave 3-inches of tops and roots.
Cook until skins slip off easily (15 minutes).
Put in cold water.
Remove skins, tops and roots.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onions in hot fat.
Cook hamburger in onions.
Pour in soup and green beans.
Cook and drain grease off.
Put in casserole dish, then spoon potatoes over the green beans to make 5 peaks. Brown in oven at 350°.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add vanilla.
Fold nuts and chocolate chips into egg whites.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil; drop
mixture onto cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Place in preheated oven; turn oven off and leave cookies in overnight.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Add all other ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and a little melted butter. Mix well and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, crumbs and butter mixture.

title: sweet-sour oriental green beans
directions: In a bowl, mix together green beans, water chestnuts, onion and bacon.
In a small bowl, mix together sugar, vinegar and bacon fat.
Stir into bean mixture to coat evenly. Pour into baking dish and let stand several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 225° for 5 to 6 hours.
Thicken with flour, if desired, to consistency when finished baking.

title: pineapple raisin cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, oleo, egg and vanilla until fluffy.
Add raisins and pineapple.
Sift in flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese-broccoli dip
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt cheeses in soup over low heat.
Add broccoli.
If desired, add a few drops Tabasco sauce.
Serve warm.

title: lite fruit dip
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Chill well.
Serve with cut up fruit.

title: vickie's hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onions lightly in 2 tablespoons fat. Add rest of ingredients. Add 1 1/2 quarts water and simmer slowly 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: brother hodge's chili con carne
directions: In large saucepan, brown beef.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter, then sprinkle evenly the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Then sprinkle the coconut evenly.
Pour the condensed milk over all this.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts or pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: white chocolate bark
directions: Spread over foil covered cookie sheet.
Cool in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter and 2 cups of sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream, beating just enough after each addition to keep batter smooth.
Spoon 1/3 of batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: philadelphia cheese steak sandwiches
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, saute peppers and onion slices in oil until tender.
Stir in steak sauce and horseradish; keep warm.
In lightly greased medium skillet over medium-high heat, cook sandwich steaks until done.
On roll bottoms, portion beef, pepper mixture and cheese.
Broil sandwich bottoms for 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts; replace tops.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: heath bar kahlua cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and allow cake to cool. Prepare pudding and refrigerate until it sets. Take half of cake and crumble it into punch bowl. Splash with coffee liqueur (approximately 1/4 to 1/2 cup). Spread half of pudding batch, then spread chocolate Cool Whip. Add half of crumbled Heath bars on top of that. (I use food chopper or food processor to chop them.) Add remaining cake (crumbled). Again splash coffee liqueur (1/4 to 1/2 cup), then pudding and finally white Cool Whip. Sprinkle remaining half of Heath bars. Great dessert for parties.

title: pantry baked beans
directions: Combine honey and mustard; add to beans and wine.
Mix well in baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chop suey hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef with celery and onion.
Add rice and brown together.
Combine all ingredients in casserole and add 1 soup can hot water.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Uncover and top with 1 cup chow mein noodles.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Do not add salt if the soy sauce is salty.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in 9 x 11-inch pan at 400° until done and golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Put all in blender and mix.

title: country blueberry pie
directions: Thaw berries until most of ice is gone.
Drain off juice. Measure and add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir into mixture of sugar, tapioca and cornstarch in saucepan.
Heat rapidly until thickening is completely.
Set aside to cool.
Add berries to cool juice.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake on lowest shelf of oven at 425° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple (do not drain).
Put into 8 x 12-inch dish and place in refrigerator.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thickened and creamy, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Remove from heat.
Pour in baked shell.
Cover with wax paper and chill.
Whip cream and add powdered sugar.
Beat until thick.
Top pie; sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oxtail soup(monastery style)
directions: Brown oxtails in butter.
Add water, salt, pepper, bay leaf and cloves and cook slowly until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours, then add bouillon.
Combine carrots, celery and onions. Blend together when finely diced.
Add to soup together with tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Do not boil. Brown flour and slowly stir into soup.
Stir constantly.
Cut lemons into small pieces.
Do not peel.
Add diced eggs, lemons and wine to soup.
Let set for 10 minutes and serve.
Serves 8.

title: lemon pie
directions: Squeeze lemons.
Stir juice, yolks and milk.
Beat until creamy and pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spicy chip dip
directions: Cook meats.
Drain, then mix in other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: crystal gardens
directions: Mix together and pour over a charcoal briquette placed in a glass dish and watch.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Brown chops in fat.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onions, green pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle rice around chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels and margarine; spread on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: marzetti
directions: Melt oleo in skillet; add ground meat.
Break up as you fry. Sprinkle garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Just before done, add green pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Cook noodles and drain. Spray casserole dish with Pam.
In bottom of bowl, spread 1 tablespoon sauce.
Add about 3 tablespoons meat mixture; put 1 cup noodles.
Repeat this twice more.
Top with tomato sauce, cheese and bread crumbs.
Cover and bake in 375° oven until cheese is hot and melted.

title: strawberry flan
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Put flan round onto large plate.
Slice strawberries and arrange on flan.
When Jell-O is cooked, pour over strawberries.
Put into refrigerator to set. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Delicious.

title: vegetable salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine vegetables.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss to coat.
Makes 4 servings!

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Blend well.
Add milk slowly. Bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Add corn and sugar.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: edie b.'s chocolate mousse
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan and remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa.
Beat egg yolks in a small mixing bowl with 1/2 cup sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in chocolate mixture, rum and vanilla.

title: punch bowl cake(serves 20 to 30)
directions: Prepare cake in 2 layers as directed.
Cool.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Crumble one layer in bottom of large punch bowl. Spread half pudding mix over cake.
Top with half the pineapple, half the strawberries and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat second layer with remaining ingredients.
Arrange cherries on top and sprinkle with pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat, drain fat.
Combine all ingredients, using enough ketchup to cover the meat well.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: greek lamb shanks
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and garlic.
Coat with flour. Brown all sides in butter or oil in frying pan.
In a casserole dish, mix soup and wine until blended. Stir in bay leaf, rosemary, basil, crushed garlic and onion slices.
Add browned shanks and baste thoroughly.
Cook in covered casserole at 350° for 2 hours. Turn and baste after the first hour.
Serve with "Near East" long grain and wild rice.
Meat will be very tender and can easily be removed from the bones. Serves 2 with leftovers.

title: oatmeal almond cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat together butter and sugar until creamy. Add combined flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats, walnuts and currants; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fat-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients, then raisins and oats; mix well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheets with foil and drop cookie dough on by teaspoonful onto the ungreased foil.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Peel off foil.
Enjoy!

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with a spoon. Pour into lightly greased baking dish and bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Serve topped with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate chip-cereal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Stir together brown sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until center is slightly firm. Cool 3 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool in pans for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Melt oleo.
Add graham crackers, peanut butter and sugar.
Mix with hands.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth with spoon.
Melt chocolate chips and spread onto top.
Let cool and cut.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut raw broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add chopped onion. Break cooked bacon into small pieces, add raisins.

title: peanut butter cookies with kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mix by hand the sweetened condensed milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick mix and vanilla.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Pick on up and see if its done on the bottom. Place candy kiss in the middle.
Put back in the oven for 1 minute.

title: chicken divan
directions: Bake chicken, celery and onion in foil.
Cool, then cut in bite size pieces.
(Use celery and onion, not the liquid.) Boil or microwave broccoli just long enough to break apart (no longer than 3 minutes).
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, pepper and lemon juice thoroughly.

title: apple pie with streusel topping
directions: Beat eggs and margarine together.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon; mix with hands.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Cut fish in cubes.
Cook celery, pepper, onion and garlic in fat until tender.
Add fish cubes and cook 10 minutes.
Dissolve beef cubes in hot water.
Add bouillon, tomatoes, tomato soup, okra and seasoning.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until fish flakes. Serve over rice.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Saute onion, green pepper,
celery
and
garlic in oil; cook until onions are
limp.
Add
catsup,
tomatoes, vinegar, brown sugar and chili
powder.
Stir in basil, oregano, cinnamon and salt.
Partially cook
meat in roasting pan with 1 cup of water at 325° for about 2 hours.
Drain juices and save for future gravy if desired.
Spoon
sauce
over meat and continue to bake for 1 to 2 hours
until
meat
is
tender.
For
more taste, omit baking with water
and
use sauce from start; cook about 2 hours, cover loosely and refrigerate overnight.
(Not in
a cast iron pan). Finish
cooking
2nd
day.
Serve
with rolls for sandwiches or use it as the main entree.

title: party ryes
directions: Mix all ingredients with just enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Place mixture by spoonfuls on Pepperidge Farm rye squares.
Place on cookie sheet and broil until cheese melts.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: chopstick tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, the tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper; toss lightly.
Place in ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top. Bake in moderate 375° oven for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with drained mandarin orange sections.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.
If doubling the recipe, bake in 9 x 12-inch dish for 25 minutes.

title: misty's one dish meal
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil.
Add onion and garlic.	Add tomatoes and beef broth.
Simmer until liquid is reduced a bit. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add kidney beans and chopped thyme, basil and rosemary.
Simmer to reduce liquids again.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press into sheet cake the graham cracker crumbs and oleo.
With spoon, mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Mix well. Pour into graham crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top and add cherries.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cooked broccoli, soup, cheese and rice.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: arabic salad
directions: Mix all vegetables.
Add seasonings.
Cut lemons in half and squeeze over salad.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo in pan and bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand 1/2 hour before eating.

title: party mix
directions: Mix cereal, peanuts and cranberries. Mix sugar and cinnamon and pour over cereal mixture. Then pour margarine over mixture and stir well. Bake at 250 degrees until crisp.

title: eggplant pie
directions: Saute tomatoes, peppers, onions and mushrooms in a little oil. Broil eggplant slices.
Brush with the 2 tablespoons olive oil, 5 minutes to a side.
Arrange in a 9-inch pie plate overlapping slices to form a crust.
Combine vegetables and place on top. Sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Combine cheeses. Sprinkle on top.
Place Parmesan on top of that.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread(makes 1 large loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with chips. Spread chicken over them. Mix all other ingredients (except cheese) in a separate bowl and pour over chicken. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterhorns
directions: Scald milk.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast and remaining sugar in small amount of warm water. Beat eggs.
Add yeast and eggs in milk mixture.
Stir in flour.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Drain cherries.
Add sprinkle of flour to cherries.
Mix all ingredients together, adding flour last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with milk poured over top.

title: salmon with balsamic sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper, then with flour.
Heat oil in large ovenproof skillet over high heat.
Add salmon, skin side up, and cook 2 minutes.
Turn fish over.
Add garlic, chopped tomatoes, clam juice, vinegar and wine. Bring to boil.
Transfer skillet to oven and roast 5 to 10 minutes until fish is opaque throughout.
Transfer salmon to plates.
Keep warm.
Continue cooking tomato mixture on stove over high heat until thickened, 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir in basil.
Spoon sauce over fillets.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 14 grams fat per serving.

title: oriental skillet supper
directions: In skillet, heat oil and brown steak; drain.
Add soup and garlic powder with water.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and onion; simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until zucchini is crisp and tender.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/2-inch thick, using a meat mallet or the edge of a saucer.
Coat flattened chicken breasts with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken breasts and brown quickly on both sides.
Add lemon juice and chicken broth and bring to a boil, gently stirring the bottom of the pan to incorporate browned bits.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease bottom of long baking dish or 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Pour
in one large can crushed pineapple, drained.	Pour over that
one can cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Sprinkle over that
one
box
white
cake
mix, dry.
Cut 1 1/2 sticks butter or	margarine into little pats all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat
milk with
butter over medium heat until butter is totally melted.
In separate bowl, beat
eggs.
Add
sugar. Gradually add in mixture of flour, baking powder and salt.
Add heated milk and butter to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and one stick of butter.
Add and mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown sausage in oil over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add onions, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Brown in butter.
Remove chicken, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings to stir in soup, seasonings and water.
Cook and stir to a boil.
Spread Minute rice in 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Pour all but 1 cup soup mixture over rice. Stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture. Bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine in a small pan. Remove from heat.
Peel the dry skin off the garlic.
Mash the cloves through a garlic press into the margarine.
Add the Italian seasoning
and oregano.
Slice the bread lengthwise and brush each half with the margarine mixture.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Put the bread on a cookie sheet butter side up.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: holiday nut balls
directions: Cream butter in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and salt.
Sift in the flour and salt mixture.
Add nuts.
Form into balls about the size of a quarter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes, watching carefully to avoid overbaking.

title: tuna casserole - family size
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain tuna and mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Stir in cooked macaroni and salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and add cheese to cover top of casserole.
Cook 10-15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: toffee bars
directions: Substitutes:
Can use butterscotch or peanut butter.

title: low-calorie chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll chicken in tomato juice mix. Place, skin side down, in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn chicken and pour remaining tomato juice over it.
Continue baking for 1/2 hour.

title: hamburg loaf
directions: Put layer of potatoes in buttered 3-quart casserole, then layer on onions, seasoning, then hamburg and seasoning.
Repeat layering until all hamburg is used.
Finish with hamburg on top. Pour sugar and tomatoes over mixture.
Cover and cook one hour in 350° oven.
Remove cover and cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: vegetarian supper
directions: Cook rice; use package directions.
In large skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add zucchini, green onion, pepper, oregano and salt.
Cook until crisp and tender, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and beans; cover and heat through.
Serve on hot rice and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 7.

title: so so dessert
directions: Mix flour, chopped nuts and margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minuets at 375°.
Cool.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, saute chopped onion.
When onion is transparent, add garlic.
Add chopped tomatoes and cover.
Bring to simmer.
Add chopped carrots.
Add lima beans, Shoepeg corn, yellow Niblets corn, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown 1 1/2 pounds ground chuck.
Add to pot.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, splat of hot sauce, 1 tablespoon basil and 1/4 cup alphabet macaroni.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Taste for salt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and save 1 cup of broth.
Mix together the stuffing mix, 1 cup broth and margarine.
Put half in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together the chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise, eggs, milk and salt and pour over dressing.
Top with remaining half of dressing.
Spread can of soup on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° or 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, pumpkin, oil, water and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing to a wire rack.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine spinach (drained), soup, cheese and onion.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix butter and stuffing.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions.
Bake two layers and split or 4 small layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut well.
Reserve 1 cup.
Stack cake with mixture.
Mix reserved 1 cup mixture with Cool Whip.
Frost top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef-like seasoning
directions: Blend ingredients fine.
Store in airtight container.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Stir corn, sugar, buttermilk, oil, cheese, pepper and onion. Beat eggs with fork; add to mixture. Add corn meal, red pepper, stir. Pour into well-greased pan. Bake until done.

title: chicken sesame
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place oil in average size skillet.
When hot, add chicken and stir-fry until partially cooked (5 minutes).
Add onion, celery, frozen peas and soy sauce. Stir-fry until onions are tender but not limp.
Add sesame seed. Serve over rice.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, 1 teaspoon of the vanilla and 1 egg; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans. Combine remaining eggs, sugar, vanilla and syrup; pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until center is firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Contains 745 calories for each of 6 servings; 560 calories for each of 8 servings; 445 calories for each of 10 servings.

title: garlic roasted red potatoes
directions: Slice garlic thin.
Combine with potatoes, oil and parsley. Place in a single layer in a flat pan, preferably enameled cast iron.
Sprinkle with fresh ground pepper.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pat in an 11 x 7-inch coffee cake pan.
Slice apples and arrange in pan.
With fork, mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of apples.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients except vanilla over double boiler until fluffy and it holds its shape, approximately 3 to 4 minutes. Add vanilla and put on cake.
It takes only 3 to 4 minutes to make, is delicious and looks pretty on a cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except last three.
Then mix flour, zucchini and walnuts into mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Bake in preheated 325° oven.

title: cheese dip for chips
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Blend in parsley, onion, celery and hot pepper sauce.

title: honey-hot pepper chicken
directions: Chop pepper finely and stir in honey and black pepper.
Rub this mixture over chicken breasts and roast them about 15 minutes at 450°.
Finish off in broiler, if not browned.
Can be served with rice or whatever you desire.

title: mexican stack-up
directions: Start with Doritos and add each ingredient in order.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Line pastry shell with pecans.
Beat eggs well.
Add corn syrup, sugar, salt and butter; mix.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for an additional 40 minutes. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: deviled underwood quiche
directions: Spread deviled ham in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle on grated Swiss cheese and chopped onion.
Beat eggs, then beat in light cream, salt and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all. Pour in graham cracker crust. Chill. Great on a hot day!

title: melted brie
directions: With serrated knife, cut hollow into bread 1/2-inch away from sides and bottom; remove from loaf.
Cut piece which has been removed from loaf into strips, 1 to 1 1/2-inch wide strips.
Mix oil and garlic.
Brush inside of shell and bread slices.
Place cut up cheese in bread shell.
Place filled shell and slices in a single layer on a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Remove bread slices.
Cook filled shell 10 minutes more and serve with grapes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: ginger applesauce
directions: Core apples; cut into eighths.
Combine apples and cider in medium saucepan.
Cook covered over medium heat until apples are soft, about 20 minutes.
Press apples through a food mill; discard skin.
Stir in sugar, candied ginger and ground ginger.
Serve warm with ice cream or refrigerate until cold and serve as a snack.

title: celebrity fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, salt, butter and milk.
Over low heat, bring to a boil and boil 6 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine the semi-sweet, German sweet chocolate and add the Marshmallow Creme and nut meats.
Pour the boiling mixture over the ingredients in the bowl.
Beat until the chocolate is completely melted.
Then pour into a greased pan.
Let stand several hours before cutting. Store in a tin box tightly covered or freezes well.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese well and add sugars and vanilla. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sugar-free banana muffins
directions: Beat milk, eggs, margarine, Splenda and vanilla in a large bowl with electric mixer for 30 seconds. Add mashed bananas and beat 1 minute. Add flour mixture. Mix with spoon until just blended. Put into greased or sprayed muffin tins or nonstick muffin pans. Bake at 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chris' chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil and saute the chicken until light brown.
Add the onion, garlic and peppers.
Saute, but do not brown.
Push sauteed vegetables aside.
Add salt as desired. Add uncooked rice and stir among the chickens.
Add the chicken broth, tomato sauce, wine and peas and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cover and place in a hot oven at 400°.
Bake until dry. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cherry-nut slices
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in flour, cherries and pecans.
If desired, chill dough for easier handling.
Divide dough into thirds on 3 sheets of waxed paper; shape each third into roll 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap; refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Heat oven to 325°.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Remove immediately.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan by directions on cake box. After baking cake punch holes in top of cake.
Drain pineapple over
the cake.
Then
put icing on top of cake, topping with pineapple. Put
in
refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: homemade bread
directions: In large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. In saucepan, combine water and oil; heat until warm, 120° to 130°. Add warm liquid to flour mixture. Blend on low speed until moistened. Blend approximately 3 minutes on medium speed. Stir in by hand approximately 3 cups flour until dough pulls away from bowl. Knead in flour (about 1 cup) until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap and towel. Place bowl in warm oven (80° to 85°) for 50 to 60 minutes or until 2 times larger. (Hint: To heat oven to proper temperature, turn oven to 400° for 1 minute, turn off and place covered bowl inside for 60 minutes.) Remove dough from oven and punch dough down to remove air bubbles. Cut in half and shape into 2 loaves. Place in 2 greased 8 x 4 or 9 x 5-inch pans and cover with towel. Place in warm oven (same as before) for 30 to 35 minutes or until 1 inch above pan. Remove towel; turn oven to 350°. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Bread should sound hollow when tapped.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine peach juice with soy sauce.
Pour over chicken and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken and bake 30 minutes or until tender.
Baste chicken frequently.
Serve peaches with chicken.

title: five pounds fudge
directions: Place chocolate chips, oleo and Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl.
In heavy 4-quart pan, bring to boil the milk and sugar. Stir constantly.
When mixture reaches full rolling boil time 8 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour over chocolate mixture in bowl and stir until well mixed.
Beat with electric mixer until fudge begins to hold shape.
Beat in vanilla and stir in nuts.
Pour in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and spread evenly with spatula. Refrigerate until cold.
Cut 60 squares.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Store in cool place.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Boil
potatoes	in
jackets,
peel
and cube.
Put in a large casserole dish. Cube cheese. Sprinkle over potatoes. Add onions, pimento,
parsley, paprika, garlic salt and croutons. Pour	melted margarine	over
all
the casserole. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. If you want to use 1/2 of recipe, use 5 to 6 potatoes and 1/2 other ingredients.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat strawberries, sugar and gelatin just enough to dissolve gelatin, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk by box directions.
Add sour cream.

title: buffet chicken wings
directions: Mix syrup, soy and dressing in large baking dish.
Set aside. Remove tips of wings to first joint and discard.
Cut remaining pieces at joint.
Place in syrup mix and let set overnight or several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning halfway through.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese thoroughly; add salt and cayenne. Gradually work in flour.
Toss on lightly floured board; roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick and cut into strips or put through cookie press. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven (350°).
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, onion soup mix and all the rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape in a loaf, about 8 x 4 x 3-inches.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: citrus quencher
directions: Mix lemon juice, lime juice and sugar together, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add orange juice.
Chill citrus base.
When ready to serve, add club soda and ice; stir.
Garnish glasses with lime slices.

title: kale and potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters (leave skin on) and boil in soup stock.
Coarsely chop kale; stir-fry and set aside.
When potatoes have softened, coarsely mash them; be sure to reserve liquid they were cooked in.
Return the mashed potatoes to the pot with the cooking liquid and stir together.
Add the stir-fried kale and some seasonings, then cook for just a few minutes longer at low heat (overcooking will rob the kale of nutrients and its rich green color).
Serving Size:
4. Preparation Time:

title: cooked creamy frosting
directions: Cook together milk and flour until thick, cool.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well until fluffy.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook at high temperature for 6 hours or until very tender.
Shred meat and serve on semi-hard rolls with meat and juices.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut a pocket on the bone side of each chop.
Combine next 7 ingredients and mix well.
Stuff each chop with mixture.
Brown chops in oil and season.
Add a little water and bake in moderate oven at about 350° about 1 hour or until tender.

title: carol's country franks
directions: Brown hot dogs in oil and remove.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, until al dente, then place hot dogs in pan again and mix.
Serve with rye bread.

title: light brownies
directions: With
mixer,
beat butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add brown sugar, then stir
in flour and nuts.
Pour in long cake pan (9 x 13 inches).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Stir in pineapple and juice. Bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes. Gradually stir 1 cup hot filling into egg yolks. Return all to pan and bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Cover with lid to keep warm.

title: mock coconut pie
directions: To cook squash, cut in half, lengthwise, and clean out seeds. Cook in microwave with 1/4 cup water for 10 minutes.
Run fork over inside of cooked squash to get spaghetti like shreds.
Place 2 cups squash in each of 2 greased and floured 8-inch pie pans. (I use Pam.)
Put all other ingredients into blender.
Pour equally over squash.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix everything together and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (no need to grease pan) and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mounds candy
directions: Melt butter.
Dump together in bowl, powdered sugar, sweetened milk, coconut and butter.
Put in refrigerator and let chill for 1 hour.
Take out and roll mixture into balls, then dip balls into melted chocolate.

title: betty's cornbread
directions: Have oil heated in cooking pans; makes 2 cake pan size.
Beat eggs.
Add baking powder, salt, flour and cornmeal.
Add butter. Pour in enough milk to make a cake like batter.
Bake at 350°.

title: grated apple pie
directions: To the beaten eggs, add the sugar, butter or oleo, dash of cinnamon, flour and vanilla and mix.
Last, add the apples.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dixie southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a bowl.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Spoon mixture into pie shell, spreading pecan halves over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes more, until a wooden pick, inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla
beat 3 minutes medium speed. Pour in greased pan and bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice with chocolate or coconut pecan icing.

title: tonkatsu
directions: Take the soy sauce and dip 1 spoon of sugar in sauce; mix. Put pork cutlet in soy sauce.
Crack egg and stir.
Put pork cutlet in egg and then into bread powder.
Wait 10 minutes or else bread powder comes off.
Put cutlet in boiling oil until it fries properly, not too soft or too hard. Slice cabbage and put on dressing.
Serve with tonkatsu sauce, cabbage and rice.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Stir in the pancake mix and corn. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
By large spoonfuls, fry in deep fat (350° to 370°) until golden brown, or fry in frypan until golden brown.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/8-inch slices, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt.
Set aside.
Mix parsley and onion.
Arrange layer of potatoes and salt lightly.
Cover with mayonnaise mixture and layer of onion and parsley on top.
Do not stir.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: taffy for taffy pull
directions: Put sugar and water in saucepan.
Stir until sugar is moistened.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 270° or soft crack stage. Do not stir candy while cooking.
Pour in shallow buttered pan. Cool enough to handle.
Take about 2 tablespoons of candy and pull until white and porous; make 1/2-inch rope.
Cut with shears. Makes 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: deluxe cheese cake(in honor of "myrtle mcklyo")
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; save syrup.
Save 1/2 cup of the fruit cocktail for garnish.
Heat 1 cup syrup and dissolve lemon jello and salt in it.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Force cottage cheese through a sieve.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold in fruit, cottage cheese, whipped cream and vanilla into the jello in the jello mixture.
Turn into crumb-lined spring-form pan and chill until firm.
Decorate top with crumbs and the 1/2 cup of drained fruit cocktail.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Mix together and put into shallow baking dish (1 1/2-quart). Then combine 2 tablespoons butter with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon lasagna salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain, rinse and drain.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine salmon and onion.
In another bowl, combine sprouts, cucumbers, chopped tomato and chestnuts.
Stir together cream cheese, salad dressing and dill weed.
Stir 1/2 cup of dressing mixture into salmon mixture.
Stir 1/2 cup of the dressing mixture into sprouts.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Slice the lemons and put in big jar.
Let set overnight. Squeeze juice from lemons.
Add to water and sugar.
Best lemonade you will ever drink.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip up the Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and whip up.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Keep refrigerated.
Use with favorite fruits.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save all juices, but orange.
If going to set all night, save bananas until morning.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
cup
boiling water.
Add cream cheese.
Mix
until dissolved.
Add cold water and chill until thickened
slightly.
Add
remaining ingredients and pour into individual molds
or an oblong dish (use glass dish 10 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch).
Chill
and
serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 to 8 molds. If molded
in
glass
dish, cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Blend milk and soup until smooth.
Add 1/4 of the soup mixture to ground beef mixture; mix well.
Shape into balls; roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in a small amount of shortening in skillet.
Place in casserole.
Pour remaining soup mixture over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yummy carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Barely cover with water.
Cook until barely tender (don't overcook).
Drain off liquid.
Add brown sugar, orange juice and spices.
Heat until sugar melts.
Add margarine if desired, but it really is good without it.
Bugs Bunny will love these!

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Spread powdered sugar on foil, heavily.
In large pan, mix sugar, syrup and water.
Stir over medium heat until it dissolves and comes to a boil.
Let cool for about 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and add cinnamon and food coloring.
Pour on foil and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Crack into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: southern yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add beaten egg and milk together.
In bowl, cut shortening into flour; add liquid to form soft dough.
Knead gently on floured board.
Roll 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Brush top with melted butter and fold into pocketbook rolls.
Place rolls in greased pan and cover with towel.
Allow to rise for 2 to 4 hours at room temperature or until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When done, brush with butter.

title: sausage-burger loaf
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl except the water; add it in as you mix for moisture so you don't bake it dry.
You can top with part of the cheese at 10 minutes before it's done. For a spicy meat loaf, use a jalapeno pepper instead of bell pepper or use both.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground meat.
Crumble cornbread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add meat, onion and eggs.
Mix well.
Cut tops from bell peppers. Put peppers in pot of boiling water and leave for a few minutes. Cut tops of bell peppers up and mix with cornbread.
Mix tomato sauce with small amount of water into mix, making it real moist. Put peppers into dressing, pressing them into it and filling the insides with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until onion and peppers are done.

title: oatmeal raisin-nut cookies for 6 weeks
directions: *Use all butter, all margarine or 1/2 of each.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until forms soft ball stage. Remove from heat; add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour onto damp cloth and shape into a roll.
Let cool, then cut into slices.

title: crescent roll coffee cake
directions: Spread 1/2 of rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese, egg, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla; beat well and spread over rolls.
Top with other 1/2 of rolls.
Bake in a 350°oven for 5 minutes.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top and bake 25 minutes more.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In hot butter in deep pot or kettle, saute onions until golden. Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika, meat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Then add 4 1/2 teaspoons paprika and enough of the water to just cover the meat.
Simmer, covered, 1 more hour or until meat is fork-tender.
Add more water towards the end of cooking time if you like extra gravy.
Serve with boiled noodles, potatoes or hot fluffy rice.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: casserole
directions: Mix meat and sauce.
Layer twice:
noodles, onion dip, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and cook at 350° until thick (about an hour).

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine for 15 to 20 minutes. Add flour; cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley and crawfish; cook 15 minutes.
Add cream and cheese.
Cook 30 minutes over low heat. Cook noodles as directed; drain and add to crawfish.
May seve as is or baked, 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
I find it tastes better baked.
Excellent also with shrimp, crab or a combination.

title: chocolate peanut butter cream pie
directions: Spoon 1/2 c. of the fudge topping into the bottom of crust. Place in freezer for 10 minutes.

title: light cake or one egg cake
directions: Cream together sugar, egg, shortening and salt.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Combine vanilla and milk.
Mix and bake at 350° until done.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash and onion.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add squash and onion and return to a boil.
Pack pickles into hot jars.
Cover with vinegar and seal.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole.
Spread the corn flakes on top and bake 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
This serves a large crowd.

title: spinach-spaghetti bake
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Combine spinach, Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan cheese, green onions, pepper and nutmeg in medium bowl.
Place half of the spaghetti mixture in a 12 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon spinach mixture over spaghetti; sprinkle with half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining spaghetti mixture.
Cover and bake 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered, until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: clam-vegetable stuffing
directions: Cook zucchini and carrot, covered, in boiling salted water 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Toss with bread cubes, mushrooms and clams or oysters.
Combine chicken broth, egg and herbs.
Pour over stuffing mixture.
Toss until moistened.
For a moister stuffing, add more broth.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until stuffing is heated through.
Serves 12, 60 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Place in a 9 x 15-inch greased pan.
Slice apples like for pie.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Put on dough.
Make mixture of sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Very good.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add brown sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut oven off and let set for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix juices.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add to juice mixture.
When ready to serve, add 2 quarts ginger ale and pineapple sherbet.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Clean and scrape carrots.
Cut lengthwise.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in boiling water until tender.
In a large skillet, cook and stir brown sugar, salt, orange peel and butter until bubbly. Add carrots.
Cook over low heat and stir occasionally about 5 minutes until carrots are glazed and heated through.

title: broccoli cauliflower tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with hot water.
Keep warm; set aside.
Cook vegetables until crisp-tender as directed on package.
Drain; set aside.
Heat oven to 400°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk; blend well.
Cook over medium heat 6 to 10 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and pepper. Spoon cooked spaghetti into prepared pan.
Top with cooked vegetables.
Pour milk mixture over top; sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture bubbles and is thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: onion and bacon balls
directions: Melt butter.
Cook bacon and onion until tender.
Add flour and stir.
Gradually add milk and cook until thick and creamy. Cool.
Stir herbs into mixture and divide into 8 portions.
Form into a ball.
Dip in beaten egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown.

title: stir-fry crab with pork and black bean sauce
directions: Finely mince ginger and garlic.
Cut entire scallion, except roots and top of green stalks, into 1/2-inch lengths.
Place crab meat in a basin of cold water.
Add few tablespoons salt and let stand 15 minutes.
In a small bowl cover black beans with water; mash.
Mix sherry, soy sauce and sugar.
Have drained crab, pork, eggs, ginger and garlic, sherry mixture, scallions and oil within reach.
Heat wok.
Add oil.
Heat oil.
Add ginger and garlic, then pork; cook until pork loses pink color.
Add crab and black beans and cook for 1 minute.
Add sherry mixture, cook for 30 seconds.
Add eggs, stir until set.
Taste for salt and pepper. Add scallions, stir until combined and heated.
Serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal, onion and salt in mixing bowl.
Add egg and water.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Drop by spoonfuls into shallow hot fat.
I do mine in a Fry Daddy.
Drain on paper towels.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all and pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: orange-baked pork chops
directions: Arrange meat in casserole. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour and top with orange slices. Pour orange juice over meat and oranges; cover. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade sweet mustard
directions: Mix vinegar and dry mustard well and let stand overnight covered and unrefrigerated.
The next day mix eggs, sugar and salt together, then add to mustard mixture.
Cook in a double boiler until thick (15 to 30 minutes).
Put in jars.
Must be refrigerated.
Makes 4 small baby jars.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Cut cheeses into 1/4-inch cubes.
Cook macaroni until al dente.
If using fresh broccoli florets, add to pasta 3 minutes before pasta is done.
Drain macaroni and broccoli.
Add Cheddar flavor cheese, Mozzarella, wheat germ, bacon bits, mustard, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into 6-cup baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour milk evenly over top and bake 18 to 21 minutes.
Serves 4.
Contains 385 calories per 1 1/4-cup serving.

title: lemon cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil, dry jello, water and eggs in a mixing bowl. Follow the instructions on cake box for baking.
While baking, mix the powdered sugar, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
When the cake is taken out of the oven, poke holes over the cake with an ice pick or chopstick and pour mixture over the cake.

title: whole wheat bread(for two loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey, oil and salt.
Add whole wheat flour and mix.
Start adding all-purpose flour and stir in enough to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Work in more white flour to a stiff elastic dough.
Put in a greased pan or bowl and set in warm place to rise.
Grease top and cover with a cloth.

title: figs with jello
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot.
Do not add water.
It makes its own juice.
Cook for 30 minutes and put in jars.

title: dessert - orange stuff
directions: Boil the 4 cups water. Add tapioca, instant pudding mix and orange Jell-O. Let cool. Add Cool Whip together with mixer, then add Mandarin oranges (drained) to mixture. Refrigerate.

title: rustic pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Press or roll 1 loaf of bread dough into 13-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Place in pie plate.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over dough.
Add mushrooms, spinach, pepperoni, onion and pizza sauce.
Roll remaining bread dough into an 11-inch circle.
Place over filling.
Pinch to seal and pull up to form a rim.
Prick top. Brush with egg and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with green salad.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine in saucepan water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello, stirring to dissolve.
Let cool until warm, then put berries in pie shell and pour jello mixture over them.
Chill until set. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart baking dish.
Beat potatoes well; add eggs and beat again.
Add oleo, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat again.
Return to baking dish and bake approximately 45 minutes at 400°.
Cover with marshmallows and put back in oven until melted.

title: honey pork
directions: Brown pork in oil in large skillet, stirring frequently, approximately 15 minutes.
Combine gravy mix, water, honey, soy sauce, vinegar, ginger and garlic salt.
Add to skillet.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add carrots, cook 10 minutes.
Add onion and peppers, cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: mommy cake
directions: Eggs have to cook.
Everything I put in there.
Put all stuff in the oven.
You color it.

title: lite snicker bars
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip well.
Add peanut butter and ice milk or ice cream.
Mix well.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut into 8 piece.
Each piece is 30 calories.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak the above ingredients for 3 hours; drain.

title: fluffy coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar, milk and flavoring.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes enough to frost tops and sides of two layers or a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake. Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices, enough to measure 4 cups.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake for 1 hour. Drain and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook 1 heaping cup of elbow spaghetti and drain.
Mix all above ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add above ingredients and toss together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Can be made and refrigerated overnight.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Place raspberry gelatin in a large bowl and add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen raspberries and pineapple.
Place half of this mixture into a 13 x 9 dish or your favorite mold.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Spread with the sour cream and pour the remaining half of the mixture on top. Refrigerate until set.
Garnish with lettuce if desired. Delicious.

title: acapulco eggs
directions: In large skillet, cook tortillas in butter until golden brown. Remove and set aside.
Add onion, cook until tender.
Drain tomatoes and reserve liquid.
Add liquid to skillet.
Cover and cook on high heat for 3 minutes, stir frequently.
Stir in meat, tomatoes and pepper.
Heat through.
Reduce to low heat, add tortillas and eggs.
Cover, cook 4 to 6 minutes or until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let set 1 minute, until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk.
Beat until light and fluffy. Sift together the dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture. Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll 1/8 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased sheet 8 to 10 minutes.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and flour and combine with raisins, dates and walnuts.
Add cold water and cook in saucepan until good and thick.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: In a large bowl combine yolks with sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Stir in bourbon and rum gradually, beating constantly. Fold in milk, egg whites and cream.
Pour mixture into punch bowl; chill.
Garnish with nutmeg when ready to serve.
Be sure to sprinkle nutmeg on top, do not dump all at once.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown the ground beef in a large nonstick skillet.
Pour off the fat.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Cover and simmer over low heat 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If sauce appears too thick, add water.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and serve.

title: dump soup
directions: "Dump" these ingredients all together and let simmer. Serve with chips and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Pour dressing over chopped vegetables.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour 9-inch cake pan.
Cut tops from persimmons and scrape pulp into food processor, process until smooth.
Measure 1 cup (reserve remaining puree for other use).
In mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar and olive oil until combined.
Sift flour, cinnamon and salt together into medium bowl.
In small bowl, combine persimmon puree with baking soda. Add to egg mixture, beat until well combined.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Add walnuts and raisins and fold into batter with rubber spatula.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 75 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Serve warm with chunky applesauce and lightly sweetened whipped cream or hard sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese and powdered dressing; form into ball.
Roll over pecan chips.
Set in refrigerator to chill.

title: mom's pasta fagioli
directions: In a large saucepan, brown chopped garlic in oil over low heat.
Remove pan from heat and add entire can of cannellini beans, including liquid.
Fill can with water three times and add water to pan. Put on medium-high and add tomato sauce, parsley and garlic powder.

title: english toffee(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and water in a 2-quart glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes until caramel colored, stirring twice.
Stir in vanilla quickly.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle chocolate on top and, when softened, spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired. Remember: Use only real butter!
When cool, break into pieces.

title: shrimp filled deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into halves.
Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in sandwich spread, mustard, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Stir in shrimp and onion.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
A pastry bag can be used to fill egg whites.
Arrange on large plate.
Cover and chill. Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: spoon oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first four ingredients on medium heat.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Spoon cookies onto cookie sheets to cool.

title: ma schley's slush
directions: First of all, if you can't say it, you've had too much!! Other name is Ma's Sly Slush.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine and melt together on medium heat the oleo and German chocolate.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add chocolate mixture.
Add chopped pecans last (optional).
Grease pie pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves, then cool.
Add the cherries and walnuts.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt. Add flour mixture to cooled fruit.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Should make 2 cakes.

title: roast whole tenderloin
directions: Marinate beef in mixture of lemon juice and oil for 1 hour at room temperature (easiest to do in a large zippered food storage bag).
Turn frequently.
Remove meat from marinade.
Combine the seasonings and rub all over the meat.
Bake 25 minutes per pound for medium-rare.
First 25 minutes at 500°, then the rest of the time at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Dredge in flour; brown on both sides in two tablespoons vegetable oil.
Pour off oil.
Slice onion and pepper into thin rings and put on top of steak in pan.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce with enough water to cover steaks.
Stir well.
Chop tomatoes in small pieces and add to pan. Simmer until steak is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water as needed.
Makes a great gravy to serve over rice.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; pour half of mixture in a 6 x 8-inch pan; set in refrigerator.
Mix sugar and sour cream. Spread over thickened mixture.
Pour the rest of the blueberry mixture over top.

title: uncooked banana pudding
directions: Mix and beat pudding until thick with Eagle Brand milk and whip until well blended, then fold in Cool Whip.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and slice bananas over top of wafers.
Pour pudding on top of that.
Let chill for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage and beef casserole
directions: Chop one small head of cabbage into bottom of a 3-quart or larger casserole.
In skillet, brown ground beef; add onion and rice.
Spoon over cabbage.
In same skillet with drippings, add tomato soup and water.
Stir in tomato paste and brown sugar. Pour over meat and cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Stir once during baking.

title: western style beans
directions: Brown meat with green pepper and onion.
Mix meat with chili sauce, catsup and pork and beans.
Fry some of bacon and mix in. Lay rest of uncooked bacon on top of mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about an hour.

title: oscar's hot sauce
directions: Pour juice from tomatoes into blender container.
Add onion, peppers and seasonings.
Blend to liquefy.
Add tomatoes.
Blend. Store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: amish pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and continue to cook slowly until done on top of stove or do not cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and prunes and nuts.
Bake in oblong pan for 45 minutes at 300°.
When cake is done, slice and spoon on sauce.

title: punch for 100
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes and cool.
Add juices and citric acid.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: easy luncheon casserole
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Combine with chicken, soup, milk, salt and 2/3 French fried onions.
Pour in a 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and top with dumplings spooned around edge.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a pan.
Dissolve sugar in melted shortening.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon soda in molasses.
Take pan off stove and add molasses mixture, mixing well.
Put 1 teaspoon baking soda in boiling water and add it to ingredients.
Mix well. Gradually stir in approximately 4 cups of flour.
Chill for at least an hour.
Roll and cut out cookies.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on a microwave platter.
Mix other ingredients (except cheese).
Spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cheese spread for sandwiches
directions: *May use milk, cream, half and half or evaporated milk.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Steam shrimp for 3 minutes and devein.
Cut up or dice Alaskan crabmeat.
Slice okra while frozen.
Remove shells from crabmeat. Drain corn.
Drain tomatoes.
Dice onions and peppers in large chunks.
Combine all ingredients in large pot (Dutch oven).
Add cornstarch to thicken as desired.
Cook for 15 minutes over medium heat (stir constantly).
Serve over white or brown rice.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until it gets thick.
Add dry jello and a few drops red food coloring.
Cover bottom of pie shells with strawberries, then pour in filling.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Boil sugar and butter. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour over layer of graham crackers and put in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: goodbye turkey casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and cook over hot water, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Pour Minute rice (right from the box) into a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine broth and salt.
Pour over rice. Sprinkle half of the cheese over rice. Top with asparagus, then turkey.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. Top with almonds, if desired.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Cook chicken until well done and remove skin and bones.
Tear in small pieces and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or use a small and a large casserole dish.
Freeze one for later use.
Combine soups and milk and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing, margarine and broth; spoon on top of the casserole.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: red hot applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve red hots and jello in boiling water.
Add cold water or ice and lemon juice.
When jello thickens, add applesauce and let set until firm.

title: foolproof beef and broccoli
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook ground beef and garlic until beef is brown.
Add onion.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boil.
Add broccoli.

title: french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Dip the bread into the liquid one at a time and then brown them in no stick fry pan.
(Do not soak the bread in the liquid).
Makes about 8 slices.
May be served with fruit, jelly or powered sugar and syrup.

title: partridge berry pie
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon juice and milk first.
Mix well, then add rest of ingredients.
Do not cook (just crusts).
Pour into crusts.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate-cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Pat remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: apple loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, beaten egg and chopped apples in separate bowl.
Combine the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: smorgasbord tuna salad
directions: Slice potatoes into a medium bowl.
Place wax beans in a second bowl.
Toss contents of each bowl with 2 tablespoons dressing. Cover a serving platter with lettuce leaves.
Place tuna in center. Pile in mounds around the tuna, the potatoes, beans and tomato wedges.
Sprinkle over tomatoes 2 tablespoons dressing.
Season all with fresh pepper.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute onion and bacon in large kettle; add water, vegetables, bouillon and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Stir mixture.
Lay fish on top; cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until veggies are tender and fish flakes easily with a fork.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk.
Blend 1/2 cup milk and flour.
Stir very gently into chowder, so as not to break fish up.
Heat; stir gently until mixture comes to a boil.
Turn heat off; let stand 30 minutes, if possible, to develop flavors, then reheat to serve.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts or 8 to 10 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook onion in oil. Add remainder and cook 1 hour. Take out bay leaf.
For a smoother sauce, puree.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put the butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place in oven to melt. Mix the balance of ingredients (except peaches) and mix well to make a batter. Remove the hot dish from the oven and pour the batter over melted butter. Spoon the peaches and then the juices evenly over the batter. Bake for about 30 minutes or until the batter is browned and has risen up around the fruit. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together by hand.
Add and mix in pecans, raisins and carrots.
Cover bottom inside of cake pan with waxed paper and grease well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes four layers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and dip balls in chocolate.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ground beef-cabbage casserole
directions: Cook beef in oil until crumbly.
Add onion, salt, rice, soup and water.
Mix well.
Place cabbage in a casserole dish and pour meat mixture over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake in a slow oven at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spaghettini ticino
directions: Do not wash the mushrooms.
Wipe them with a damp paper towel and slice them, reserving the stems for stock or soup.
In a large skillet heat 3 tablespoons of butter.
When it is hot, add the mushroom slices and cook them without browning for 2 to 3 minutes. Add the onions and garlic and cook the mixture for 2 or 3 minutes. Season with salt and white pepper.
Remove from heat and reserve. In a small skillet heat 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add the Prosciutto, cover the skillet and cook for 5 minutes over low heat. Remove from heat and reserve.

title: moist brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs. Using a wooden spoon, beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: country cookies
directions: In large bowl cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add flour, sprinkle baking soda and salt.
Beat until flour can't be seen.
With wooden spoon stir in oats and coconut. Drop by tablespoon 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges begin to brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: busy day pie
directions: *Use brown sugar with pineapple.

title: barbecued dove
directions: Wash dove breasts
and	place
in a closed 1 x 1/2-inch welded wire
basket.
Arrange
approximately
1	foot
above "white" charcoal (with all starter burned off).
Sop frequently with mix to keep moist.
Remove breasts from brisket (about medium rare). Do not overcook!

title: sweet yogurt dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve cold.
Great over sliced fruit.

title: lo-cal zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into oiled or sprayed casserole. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: *If using frozen pie shells, this recipe fills 2.
Bake as pie shell package directs.

title: lemon delight dessert
directions: Break cake into bite-sized pieces. Mix lemon juice with sweetened condensed milk and stir until well mixed. Whip cream; put the 2 together. Put 1/2 of the cake in a 9 x 13 pan, then half the mixture. Top with the other 1/2 of the cake pieces and the rest of the mixture. Sprinkle top with coconut. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet and sour poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Can make 4 days ahead of time.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sponge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Line pan with wax paper. Pour in mixture and cook at 300° to 325° for 14 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large, heavy saucepan.
Add egg yolks and enough of the milk to make a thick paste.
Gradually add all the milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter; beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Add meringue and brown in hot oven.
Cool several hours before cutting.
(Makes excellent chocolate pudding, too!)

title: asparagus wrapped in smoked ham
directions: In a medium pan place one inch of water on the bottom.
Pour in lemon juice.
Place a metal steam in pan; cut the asparagus into equal lengths and arrange in the pan.
Add pepper and butter on top.
Steam for 5 minutes.
Cut smoked ham into twenty strips, one oz. package should be sufficient.
Remove the asparagus from steamer.
Cool for two minutes.
Wrap the asparagus diagonally with the smoked ham.
Serve immediately or can be served cool. Servings 10.

title: oven-herb chicken
directions: Dip chicken in mixture of salad dressing, softened butter and paprika.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs and place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Sprinkle paprika over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in large skillet until browned. Add broccoli, pepper and chestnuts; stir-fry until crisp-tender. Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ginger. Add to skillet.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute.

title: weekend brunch
directions: Fry bacon on medium heat until crisp; drain.
Remove bacon and drippings.
In same pan, cook onion in butter on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring, until thick.
