Stir in cheese, bacon, rice and zucchini. Pour into lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: eggnog glazed cookies
directions: In a 3-quart mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar and egg.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Stir in vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and nutmeg until mixed well.
Force the mixture through a cookie press onto an ungreased cold cookie sheet.
Bake in the center of a 375° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
While still warm, dip top of each cookie in the Egg Nog Glaze.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in order lettuce, onions, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar, salt, pepper and dressing.
Mix and put on top of layers in pan.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Let sit 24 hours before serving.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Brush chicken, using 1/2 mixture.
Place chicken in oven and turn down to 375°.
Bake 30 minutes.
When half done, brush with remaining mixture.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples and dry ingredients together.
Put into pie shell. Top with pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour mix into pie pan.
Bake until knife blade comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken or beef enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, put Velveeta, soup and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted. Put meat on tortillas. Spoon cheese (about 2 tablespoons). Roll up; put in pan seam side down. Pour remaining sauce over tortillas. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy doughnuts
directions: Cut holes in center of each biscuit.
Deep fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Shake doughnuts in sugar mixture.
May use powdered sugar or frosting. Makes 8 to 10.

title: easy pickled beans
directions: Cook beans until done and cool.
Pack in jars.
Stir ingredients until salt dissolves.
Fill each jar with mixture. Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread beans in a glass (deep dish) pie plate.
Mix mashed avocados, lemon juice and salt, then spread on top of the beans. Mix the sour cream, taco seasoning and the Miracle Whip (if used). Place this on top of the avocados.
Now, layer the rest of the ingredients in order as listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended. Spread in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate. Spoon pizza sauce evenly over top. Sprinkle with chopped pepperoni and top with chopped green onions.

title: jamaican red beans and rice
directions: Break and remove coconut from shell; wash and grate coconut very fine.
Add water to grated coconut; mix and squeeze milk from the grated nut.
Get at least 4 cups of milk.
Place milk in pot. Add salt to taste, onion and green onion and bring to a boil.
Add rice and water from cans of kidney beans.
Return to boil, then cover and simmer on low heat.
When rice is almost cooked, add beans and finish cooking.

title: good lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Add milk, butter, rind, juice, and egg yolks. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick. Cool. Fold in sour cream and lemon flavoring. Refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream cheeses together.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup nuts.
Return to refrigerator until firm enough to handle easily.
Shape into balls and roll in nuts and store in refrigerator.

title: fruitcake (quick bread)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12-cup fluted tube or 10-inch tube pan.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In the bottom of a buttered 2-quart casserole, arrange the chili peppers, cut into pieces, about 2 inches square.
Cut the cheese into long fingers and arrange in an even layer over chili peppers.
Beat eggs slightly, then beat in milk, flour and salt; pour over cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until custard is set.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp until fine.
Stir shrimp into softened cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and grated onion and add to shrimp mixture.
Add juice of 1 fresh lemon into dip.
Use 2 drops of red food coloring.
Mix together.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: chocolate chip delight
directions: In coffee cup or similar size container, fill with enough milk to cover size of cookie.
Dip each cookie with just enough to "bubble" a second or two.
If you hold it in too long, it will fall to pieces.
After cookie is wet with milk, layer in a flat square covered container.
When a layer is completed, spread Cool Whip on top of cookies, being sure not to "mix" with cookies.
Continue with process until cookies are gone, or container is full.
End with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.
Kids love it so much, they call it "ice cream".

title: greg's chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients and heat on stove.
Brush on chicken several times while cooking on grill.
For less tangy, use 1/2 cup oil and 1/4 cup vinegar.

title: 7-layer taco salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order as shown in a dish approximately 9 x 13-inch size.
Let set for approximately 30 minutes before serving to allow the dressing to seep through all layers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together the peanut butter and sugar; spread on bottom of pie crust.
Add pudding on top of peanut butter.
Cover top of pie with Cool Whip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in medium skillet over medium heat until beef is browned and vegetables tender (about 10 minutes). Stir in ketchup, water, mustard, vinegar and brown sugar; heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until mixture is thickened (about 5 minutes). Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon onto toasted buns. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and cook in microwave until tender; scrape inside of zucchini into a bowl.
Add chopped onion (to taste), butter, salt, pepper and Pepperidge Farm bread crumbs. Mix together and stuff back in zucchini hulls.
Put cheese slice on top and bake at 350° to 400° until cheese melts, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tender baked fish
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Cut butter into tiny pieces and place in pan.
Place fish on top of butter.
Put 3 thin slices of lemon on top and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sprinkle spices over fish; pour milk around fish.
Top fish with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° until fork-tender, about 25 minutes.

title: creamed tomato gravy
directions: Brown flour in oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Mash tomatoes and add milk.
Cook until thick.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over vegetables until they soften and pack in a quart jar.

title: spicy mustard
directions: Combine vinegar and dry mustard;
allow to stand overnight. Pour into blender.
Add eggs and sugar;
blend well, then cook in double boiler until thick.
Refrigerate.
Makes approximately 24 ounces.

title: pie crust
directions: With a blender or fork mix together first four ingredients.
In a separate dish beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened. Then with hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling into desired shape.
Dough can be left in refrigerator for up to 3 days or it can be frozen until ready to use.

title: champagne jelly
directions: Combine sugar and champagne in large Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves (do not boil).
Remove from heat; stir in liquid pectin.
Skim off foam with metal spoon. Quickly pour hot jelly into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch of headspace; wipe jar rims.
Cover at once with metal lids and bands.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Let stand 8 hours.
This jelly makes a nice party favor or gift.
Yield:
5 half pints.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Place the caramels and water in top of double boiler.
Heat, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and the sauce is smooth.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Follow directions on jello box. When jello is beginning to set, add carrot, marshmallows and walnuts.

title: hawaiian coconut spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and preserves, mixing until well blended. Add coconut; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with nut bread slices.

title: amy's devilish mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Mix deviled ham, croutons and chopped mushroom stems together.
Stuff mushrooms; arrange in round pan together.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: topless sour cream apple pie
directions: Cut apples.
Combine sour cream, sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and egg.
Beat with mixer until sugar is dissolved.
Blend in apples.
Spoon into pastry.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Crumble Brown Sugar Topping on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until topping and crust are browned.

title: avocado egg salad
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and hot pepper sauce until well blended. Toss lightly with remaining ingredients until evenly coated with dressing. Cover - chill to blend flavors.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients before combining.
Combine juices; add ginger ale last.
Serve immediately after adding the ginger ale. If desired, omit 1 quart ginger ale and add a bottle of gin, vodka or light rum.

title: onion rings
directions: Cut onions 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick.
Soak in the cup of milk for two hours.
Drain well.
Bake batter with the flour, salt, butter, eggs and the milk the onions were soaked in.
Dip rings one at a time; fry one at a time in Crisco.
Drain when browned.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes; remove from fire.
Add butter, vanilla and salt.
Serve warm over Cottage Pudding.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt together and add to shortening.
Mix well.
Stir in melted chocolate until blended. Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bunch-of-banana banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In a bowl, mash bananas.
You should have 1 cup.
Beat in sugar, then egg and butter.
In another bowl, stir together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add banana mixture and stir just until all flour is moistened.
Pour batter in prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
It is done when a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
A crack down the center is characteristic of this type of bread.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes, then turn onto rack to cool completely.
If you wait a day before slicing, the bread will be easier to slice and more flavorful.

title: nut kisses
directions: Chop the nuts very fine (peanuts or pecans).
Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in the sugar a little at a time.
Fold in the vanilla, salt and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 40 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen Nut Kisses.
Store in tight container.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix broccoli, onion, eggs, butter, 1 cup cheese and salt.
Add corn muffin mix; mix and blend thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until mixture tests done.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, carrots, salt, pepper and margarine until tender.
Whip cream of chicken soup and milk.
Pour into potatoes.
Simmer an hour or so.

title: meat-potato quiche
directions: In
a
9-inch pie pan, stir together vegetable oil and potatoes. Press evenly
into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, until just beginning to brown.
Remove from oven.
Layer on grated cheese and chicken.
In
a
bowl, beat together milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture onto other ingredients. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley flakes.
Return
to oven and bake at 425° for 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash, onions, bell peppers and salt.
Cover with ice. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.

title: shrimp in lemon garlic sauce
directions: Clean, peel and devein shrimp and set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add next 8 ingredients to bowl and top with cover.
Process for 30 seconds or until well mixed.
With processor running, add butter through food chute; process 1 minute or until sauce is thickened.
Set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Drain shrimp and dredge in flour mixture.
Fry shrimp in hot oil until golden brown.
Turn once; drain.
Arrange shrimp in 4 or 5 individual baking dishes and top with sauce.
Broil shrimp 30 to 45 seconds. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: eggplant festiva
directions: Heat olive oil in frying pan over medium high heat.
Add butter and spices; mix thoroughly.
Skin and cube eggplant.
Saute in olive oil until soft (5 to 10 minutes).
Grease or spray a large (9 x 13 x 2-inch) casserole dish.
Cover bottom with bread crumbs; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Drain eggplant; put into saucepan. Add diced onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir taco/picante sauce in mixture.
Heat 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat.

title: hawaiian low calorie pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch with water.
Mix milk and coconut flavoring; bring to a boil and add cornstarch mix while stirring.
Then add coconut and pour into bowl to cool.
Serve cold.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: Slice or half washed mushrooms lengthwise.
In butter, in large skillet over low heat, saute onion until tender; add mushrooms.
Saute over medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, lemon juice, celery salt, then milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing for several hours. Drain.
Cover with 1/2 package of onion soup mix and 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Add mushroom soup, remaining onion soup mix and milk (and mushrooms, if desired).
Mix thoroughly.
Place chicken whole or in strips on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butterscotch granola
directions: Melt oleo and mix everything except butterscotch chips. Spread evenly on 2 large cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes for the first 30 minutes and then every 5 minutes until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water. Saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add this to the vegetables already cooked.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine and mix well.
Drop in muffin cups (small) and bake at 350° until done (maybe 7 minutes or until browned a little).
Turn out on wire rack to cool. Store in airtight container.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, combine the egg and milk. Add melted butter. Make a well in the dry ingredients. Pour milk mixture in the well stirring just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in blueberries. Spoon into 12 buttered muffin tins. Bake 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips 2 inches long.
Heat shortening and brown meat.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Stir in peppers.
Simmer, covered, until peppers are tender.

title: nut and fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs. Put all nuts and fruit in a large pan.
Sift dry ingredients over fruit, nut mixture.
Mix with hands until all flour is mixed in well.
Pour eggs over all.
Mix good with hands. Pack in 5 loaf size pans. Fill about 3/4 full. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Adjust time for larger or smaller pans.

title: italian strip cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla in a large bowl for about five minutes with an electric beater.
Add baking powder and flour and beat until evenly mixed (about one minute).
Put the mixture and the walnuts on a floured pastry board and knead lightly to mix (walnuts should be left in large pieces).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream and beat together the first 4 ingredients, then add the last 5 ingredients.
Roll in balls and then sugar. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: crab and swiss on sourdough
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Flake.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon 2 teaspoons crabmeat mixture on each slice of sourdough (cocktail size).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Quick and delicious.
Makes lots.

title: barbecue tuna
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in skillet with a tablespoon of butter. Stir in broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and salt.
Spread rice over bottom and up side of casserole.
Spoon broccoli mixture over rice.
Sprinkle with paprika or cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tempura
directions: You will need the following equipment:
skillet, spatula, mixing bowls, forks, measuring spoons, paper towels, pot holder and spatter screen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers crumbs with 1 cube oleo and press in bottom of large pan.
Combine powdered sugar, 2 cubes of oleo and cream cheese.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Spread over unbaked crust.
Put a layer of sliced bananas over mix and crushed pineapple (drained) over the bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over fruit.
Top with cherries and chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all stuff together and use to cover chicken or beef.

title: baked cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces and boil in slightly salted water until almost tender.
Remove from heat, drain and pour into a 13 x 2-inch greased casserole dish.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 3/4 cup tomato sauce in bowl, mixing well.
Pat meat mixture into 9 x 13-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with cheese and mushrooms.
Roll as for jelly roll, sealing edge and ends.
Place seam side down in 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Pour off drippings. Spoon remaining tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sun dill pickles
directions: Pour over sliced pickles.
Sit outside in sun for 2 days. Refrigerate after bringing them in.

title: banana pudding(uncooked)
directions: Beat instant pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip to pudding.
In a large dish, put layer of wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Repeat with a second layer.
Put remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or for about 6 hours.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and sliced potatoes round.
Layer a 13 x 9-inch pan with potatoes.
Add pork chops, then onion rings and then another layer of potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Lay pats of butter on top.
Pour milk over top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° until potatoes and pork chops are done.

title: herb blend(use instead of salt for seasoning.)
directions: If using full leaves of oregano, marjoram, rosemary or sage, crush a little bit at a time with the back of a spoon.
Mix well and spoon into a container with a tight cover.

title: popovers(12 popovers)
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Grease muffin pan and sprinkle Parmesan cheese in pan.
Mix milk and flour in blender; add and flip blender to mix a little at a time.
Add salt and buzz blender. Add eggs, one at a time, and flip, flip, and flip each one.
Pour batter (like heavy cream) into muffin pan 3/4 full.
Pop in oven and bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Do not open oven.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes longer.

title: little porcupines
directions: Wash rice and drain.
Combine rice, meat, onion, green pepper and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Form into small balls.
Heat tomatoes and other ingredients in a heavy skillet (including remaining salt).
Drop meat balls in and cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in greased pan; salt and pepper.
Spread kraut on top of chicken.
Place cheese slices on top.
Pour dressing over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry mixture.
Knead dough on floured board until it holds together. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and dip biscuits in melted oleo or butter and place on pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato salad nicoise
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Peel and cube potatoes and add next 5 ingredients.
Toss with Vinaigrette Dressing.
Cover.
Chill several hours or overnight, stirring gently once or twice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together until oranges and batter are mixed well. Bake in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serves 4 people.

title: fried okra with tomatoes
directions: Combine okra, salt, pepper, flour and cornmeal in large mixing bowl.
In large skillet, add oil.
When hot, pour okra mixture in and reduce heat.
When okra is about half done, add tomatoes and continue to allow okra to brown until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with chicken.
Place broccoli on top, then the cheese.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over cheese.
Mix together stuffing and melted butter.
Place on top. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: 1,2,3,4 marble cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Cream for 10 minutes.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. In medium bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Gently beat in flour mixture to creamed mixture in four additions, alternately with milk until smooth after each addition.
Turn half the batter into prepared pan (tube pan).

title: broccoli with sour cream sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain. Melt butter or margarine; add lemon juice and sour cream.
Heat over medium heat until hot.
Pour over broccoli.

title: shirley snider's mom's meringue
directions: Microwave cornstarch, sugar and water until thick, approximately 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/4 cup melted margarine and corn flakes.
Spread in 10 x 15-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle with 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in a bowl.
Stir in salt and oil.
Gradually stir in flour.
Smooth and knead dough until elastic.
Brush top with oil.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar, mixing until well blended.
Blend in 1 egg and set aside.
Combine water, margarine and cocoa in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add combined remaining sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Blend in remaining eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter several times for marble effect; sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool; cut into squares.

title: western chili casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add 3/4 cup onion and celery; cook until tender. Drain off excess fat.
Add chili and pepper.
Heat.
Place layer of chips in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of chili mixture, chips and cheese.
Save 1/2 cup chips and 1/4 cup cheese for trim.
Sprinkle center with reserved cheese and onion. Cover and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Border with chips.

title: butter mints
directions: Mix with your hands.
Form into small balls and press with a fork to flatten.
Lay each ball on waxed paper and flatten each one as you make the balls so they do not set up too fast. Chill and store, but be sure to put waxed paper between the layers of mints.

title: ground beef with fried rice
directions: Brown rice in bacon drippings.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise in 1-inch pieces. Cook until tender. Meanwhile, combine the next four ingredients and add orange juice. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Boil for 1 minute. Stir in butter and pour over carrots.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix together white sugar and 1 cup less 3 tablespoons of cooking oil.
Now add eggs, one at a time.
Now add buttermilk. Mix.
Mix flour with baking soda, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and salt. Sift all dry ingredients together, then mix with liquid. Now add blackberry jam, vanilla and nuts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender; drain and mash.
Season to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients, reserving half of the stuffing which has been mixed with melted butter. Line a casserole with reserved stuffing.
Set aside enough stuffing
to sprinkle on top.
Fill casserole with squash mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. May be prepared the day before and baked when needed.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef well and drain.
Add cheese. Spoon 1 tablespoon of mixture on party rye bread.
Can be frozen and heated up in microwave oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: strawberry-pretzel dessert
directions: Combine butter with 3 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Cream 1 cup sugar with cream cheese.
Add the Cool Whip. Spread over cooled pretzel mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; pour over cream cheese layer. Chill.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels, then crumble. Mix bacon, mayonnaise and cheese together. Place mixture on cocktail rye. Heat until cheese is bubbly at 350°. Yields 20.

title: ham-cheese pretzel pick-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine cheese, ham, horseradish, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well. Shape into 48 (3/4-inch) balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
To serve, insert 1 pretzel stick into each cheese ball.

title: neiman-marcus
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into oblong baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on top of first layer (crust).
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: Rub wooden bowl with cut garlic clove (discard garlic).
In bowl, combine spinach, mushrooms and sliced eggs.
Cover and chill.
In a screw-top jar, combine salad oil, lemon juice, salt and a few dashes freshly ground pepper.
Cover and shake to mix. Chill in refrigerator.
Combine oil and lemon mixture right before eating.
Crumble bacon over top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tiramisu (light)
directions: With serrated knife, cut pound cake into 1/2-inch slices (either 6 lengthwise or 11 to 12 crosswise slices).
In large bowl, beat together the mascarpone cheese, cream cheese and confectioners sugar just until blended.
Beat in the Kahlua until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Arrange 1/2 the pound cake slices in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan, trimming slices to fit and fill as needed.
Brush slices with 1/2 cup coffee.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture over top.
Sift 2 tablespoons cocoa powder over cheese mixture.
Repeat layering with cake slices, coffee and cheese mixture and end with 1 tablespoon cocoa powder.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Mix bread cubes with butter, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and brown sugar.
Arrange in alternate layers with apples in slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook on high for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours or until apples are tender.
Serve warm with cream, hard sauce or ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream together the cheeses and season mix.
Shape into a ball and chill, then roll in chopped pecans.
Place in the middle of a serving tray and surround with your favorite crackers and serve.

title: mounds cake
directions: Make 2 layers.
Split layers and let cool.
When cool, spread with coconut filling.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: *If you like very sweet, use sweetened; otherwise use in own juice.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all-bran and boiling water and let set.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add Bran Buds, bran mixture, flour, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use as needed.
May be kept up to one month.
Bake without stirring again.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken a la mushroom(good served with rice pilaf and a salad)
directions: Cook chicken in oil with chopped garlic in a frying pan.
When it is done, add to roasted peppers mixture.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck, Italian sausage, onion, green pepper and spices. Add tomato paste to mixture; stir well. Add stewed tomatoes.
Let simmer about 30 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese and eggs.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a large lasagne pan, layer sauce, noodles, Swiss cheese and cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Repeat for second layer, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup; don't boil.
Add gelatin and cheese and beat until smooth, then cool.
Add other ingredients.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift flour and soda into batter mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Pour half the batter in a greased angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle evenly with half the nut mixture.
Repeat process, topping with nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thick and clear.
Stir a little of this hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Return to saucepan; cook and stir for 2 minutes longer. Remove from heat; add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into cooled, baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Spread over pie filling and be sure to seal well to crust.
Bake at 425° for about 5 minutes, until golden brown.

title: forgotten roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of heavy foil an arrange vegetables around it.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, then spoon undiluted mushroom soup on top.
Wrap loosely with the corners of the foil, making sure the sides and top are sealed.
Place in roaster pan and bake at 275° for four hours.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add milk. Blend well. Melt butter in small bread pan. Pour batter in pan. Spoon cherries over batter; not too close to edge. Bake 30 minutes at 400° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Spray Pam in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Split Twinkies and line bottom of dish, marshmallow side up.
Prepare pudding mix but reduce milk by 1/3 the amount for a stiffer consistency.
Set aside.
Drain a small amount of juice from pineapple.
Spread the pineapple and remaining juice over Twinkies.
Cover pineapple with pudding.
Put bananas on top of pudding and spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.
Serve when cold.

title: bell pepper delight
directions: Brown ground beef, and add bell pepper (chopped), onion, garlic salt and tomato sauce in a frying pan.
After rice is cooked, pour into a deep baking dish.
Add the prior mixed ingredients and stir until rice is mixed well.
Top with a thin layer of cheese and put into the oven until the cheese is melted.

title: herbed oatmeal pan bread
directions: Grease 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bring water to boil and stir in oats.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 3 Tbsp margarine.
Cool.

title: omelet sandwich
directions: Coat bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Line bottom of dish with 8 bread slices, cutting them to fit.
Arrange the cheese, ham and remaining bread slices over top; set aside.

title: halloween sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add, alternating with milk.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll a portion of dough at a time to 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured board.
Cut, using 1-pound coffee can.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until browned.
Decorate as pumpkins.

title: homemade pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast in 1 cup of warm water, then add your flour, salt and shortening.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscorch morsels over low heat.
Mix in noodles and peanuts and stir until well coated.
Spoon out on waxed paper.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Make French vanilla pudding according to directions.
Mix together the cream cheese, soft margarine, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Blend with pudding.
Spread half of the cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pudding on top and top with remaining crumbs. Refrigerate.

title: saltine and peanut butter candy
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and crushed crackers.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch slightly buttered pan.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: squash and pepper skillet
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add squash, red pepper and garlic; stir fry for 12 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are crisp tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
(One serving prepared with salt equals 53 calories, 8 grams carbohydrate.)

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; pour melted oleo over all and sprinkle with all spices.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours covered; uncover and bake 1/2 hour more.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with crumbled nacho cheese Doritos; add Old El Paso sauce, onion and olives and top with cheese.
Put back into oven until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir soup until smooth. Gradually add milk.
Mix beans and 1/2 can onions into soup mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbling.
Sprinkle remaining onions over top and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: oniony rice
directions: Preheat oven
to 375°.	Saute onion, rice and mushrooms in margarine
in
a
skillet
until rice begins to turn a bit brown and
onion	is tender.
Pour the mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish
and
add
soup.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for about an hour or until all soup has been absorbed.

title: texas bean dip
directions: Arrange
the following in
layers into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan or any large tray or plate.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and bacon in pastry shell.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese-bacon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut into wedges.
Serve hot.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all together. Chill and serve.

title: lefsa-mabel and irene
directions: Heat sugar, butter, salt, milk and evaporated milk in saucepan and add to potatoes.
Cool potato mixture overnight (secret of lefsa is to keep the dough thoroughly cold).
Add 5 cups of flour. Take walnut size pieces of dough.
Roll out on floured board until paper thin.
Cook on griddle slowly (too hot and it browns but is not cooked through).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer on low heat at least 30 minutes.

title: heart healthy stir-fry
directions: Rub fish with Puritan oil.
Roll fish in corn flake crumbs. Season fish with salt and pepper.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese; blenderize pimentos.
Mix all together until creamy.
Keeps approximately 1 1/2 weeks.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with cherry halves.

title: spanish rice with shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in 2-quart casserole. Cover.
Microwave at High (100%) for 10 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium (50%).
Microwave until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, 28 to 35 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: eggnog supreme
directions: Combine egg yolks and sugar.
Beat until lemon colored and thick, then slowly add brandy, rye or rum and light cream.
Beat to blend well and chill one hour or overnight to allow egg to mellow.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Heat and stir until boiling, margarine, water and cocoa. Remove from heat; add salt, sugar, flour, eggs and soda.
Add sour cream.
Pour in sheet cake pan, greased.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: carrot and beet cake
directions: Mix as listed; fold in egg whites last. Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes
or until done at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in bowl as written.
Layer and spread to edges Miracle Whip, cheese and sugar.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Just before serving, mix together. Make sure bowl is sealed tight in refrigerator.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Wash beans and drain.
Pack beans into clean, hot jars; add pepper, mustard seed, dill seed and garlic.
Combine vinegar, water and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Pour boiling liquid over beans, filling to 1/2 inch from top of jar.
Adjust jar lids.
Process in boiling water for 5 minutes.
(Jars will cool the water, so start to count processing time as soon as water in canner returns to boiling.) Remove jars and re-tighten lids if necessary.
Set jars upright several inches apart on a wire rack to cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Heat sugar, flour and juice until sugar melts.
Add cheese until it melts (low heat).
Place pineapple chunks in casserole dish.
Pour mixture over top.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top. Slice stick of butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican style chicken and rice
directions: Saute salt and peppered chicken in small amount of oil.
Add onion, cilantro, bell pepper, and carrot; saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until water is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Put oil, strawberries and juice and eggs in and mix well.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans or muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve warm with strawberry cream cheese.

title: caramel pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Cut each section in half lengthwise.
press dough in bottom of ungreased 13x9 in. pan. Bake at 375 for 10-18 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 15 minutes.
In large sauce pan, combine 1 c. chocolate chips, and 1 c. of dip.
Cook over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and pecans. Spread over crust.
In a small sauce pan, combine remaining 1 cup chips and 1/2 cup dip.
Cook over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring constantly.
Spread over cereal mixture. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into 36 bars.

title: un-fried crabcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rinse the crabmeat under cold running water and drain, making sure to remove any filament or shell. Spray the vegetable oil over the baking sheet 3 times to coat.
In a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs, and stir in the crabmeat.
Using 1/4 cup for each crabcake, form the mixture into 8 cakes.
Roll each in the reserved bread crumbs and place on the prepared baking sheet. Coat the crabcakes lightly with the cooking spray.
Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven and bake the crabcakes for about 5 minutes per side until brown.
Fat per serving, 2.4 grams. Calories per serving, 252.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, dressing mix and grated cheese. Layer these ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the shrimp, together.
It will form a paste-type filling.
Place the shrimp in a shallow baking pan.
Dot the shrimp with the butter mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 people.
Calories:
1 million.

title: picnic pasta
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bake at 350° in a covered Corning Ware dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour until it bubbles.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour.
Mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth.
Pour over partially cooled crust.
Bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Chill.

title: stir-fry vegetable pancake
directions: Blend with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour mix into skillet.
Bake for 10 minutes in 450° oven.
Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake for another 10 minutes.
While pancake is baking, melt 2 to 3 tablespoons butter in pan and saute vegetables and spices of your choice.
Spoon vegetables over the pancake.
Can add grated cheese and salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Drain and mash candied yams in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well by hand.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes or until mixture is firm.
Remove from oven and place topping on casserole.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda to buttermilk and then add to sugar mixture alternately with flour.
Bake at 315° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika.
Brown in oleo.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and bell peppers.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, soy sauce and water. Add to meat mixture.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Stir gently.
Serve over rice with a green salad.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken a'la creole
directions: Rinse the chicken well.
Simmer the chicken to make stock. After the chicken is boiled, remove from stock.
Let cool, then debone and save meat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix and pour over butter melted in pan.
Mix fruit and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spoon over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add next five ingredients and mix well. Put half of crushed Doritos in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Add olives and other half of Doritos. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more. Top with sour cream to serve.

title: broccoli and swiss bake
directions: In a saucepan, cook broccoli until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.
In another saucepan, melt butter, add flour.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in onion.
Gradually add milk; bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat; stir in cheese, eggs and broccoli.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together in quart size jar.
Shake well.
Refrigerate. Shake before using.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Cook in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: copper pennies marinated carrots
directions: Mix and pour over carrots.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine white sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Melt butter and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Quarter each biscuit and place in bowl with sugar and cinnamon to coat.
Place coated biscuits in Bundt pan.
Pour melted sugar and butter over top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry crumble
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread undrained pineapple in pan then add layer of blueberries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Drizzle butter over all and top with pecans and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After 25 minutes, put spoon down through all in many places to let juice come up.

title: fat free old fashioned chicken dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits until fine.
Mix poultry seasoning with bread.
Stir-fry celery and onion in Pam cooking spray, until tender.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Add cream and enough vegetable broth to make mixture like cornbread batter.
Pour in pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Drain and mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots into lengthwise strips and cook until tender.
In large skillet, cook and stir brown sugar, salt, orange peel and margarine until bubbly. Add carrot strips.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until carrots are glazed and heated through.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and while still hot, add jello.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In a bowl, cream the butter.
Gradually add the sugar.
Beat well.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to the first mixture, combining well into a dough.

title: cabbage chopped suey
directions: Put drippings in skillet.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Garnish with strips of crisp bacon.

title: italian beef
directions: Remove excess fat from roast and cut roast into large chunks. Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer until meat can easily be shredded with a fork (approximately 8 hours).
Serve meat with juice on kaiser or other style hard rolls.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and heat all ingredients, except cucumbers and onions, until the sugar has dissolved.
Pour over sliced cucumbers and onions in gallon jug and let stand in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: barbecued sauce for chicken, beef or pork
directions: Saute onions in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Brush on grilled chicken or chop barbecue pork or beef and add to sauce.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix well in large mixing bowl and place in a greased, floured cookie sheet (11 x 16-inch) for 30 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick after 30 minutes and set aside to cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add 1 cup of pecans and all other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll in rest of pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 large or 2 medium size balls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix
ingredients
together and form into a ball.
Chill for 3 hours.
Roll into finely chopped walnuts and chill for 1 more hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine hot water and lemon jello together; cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Whip Pet milk.
Combine jello mixture with the cream cheese mixture; fold in Pet milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each egg.
Add flavoring and add 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup cream, 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup cream and 1 cup of flour.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, soup mix and egg together.
Make into meatballs and brown in pan.
Drain on paper towels.

title: carrot pineapple mold
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Place reserved pineapple liquid in small bowl.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Add pineapple liquid to jello.
Refrigerate and chill several hours or until partially congealed.
Stir in pineapple, carrots, cheese and pecans.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: pizza cups
directions: You will need a skillet, a wooden spoon and a 12 or 2 (6) cup muffin pans.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter in mixer until smooth.
Add granulated sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add enough flour until mixture sticks together.
Gather dough and divide into 6 portions with minimum handling and using wax paper or foil.
Shape each dough into small log.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight or until firm enough to slice.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces and place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown on bottom and then cool.
Blend powdered sugar with lemon juice until smooth.
Frost top of each shortbread cookie.
Garnish with slices of maraschino cherries if desired.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: pizza pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, saute the beef, onion, garlic and the mushrooms until the meat is browned and the mushrooms are tender.
Add the pepperoni, basil, oregano and red pepper flakes.
Stir to combine.
Turn the mixture into 8 or 9-inch pie pan lined with one crust.
Top meat mixture with 1/2 grated Parmesan and the Mozzarella.
Cover evenly with the tomato slices and sprinkle remaining Parmesan on top. Cover with crust and flute edges and make vents.
Bake
for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put tomatoes in last, so it won't get soggy.
Toss gently.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together at low speed until well blended, then beat on high speed until light and fluffy.
Place in greased 9-inch casserole. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Last 10 minutes, top with onion rings if desired. Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Mix in egg and onion.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, mushroom soup and milk together.
Mix dressing, oleo and seasoning together.
Layer 1/2 of dressing in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Add chicken and top with rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and lima bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare beans according to package directions.
Spray 1 1/2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place beans in dish.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, tomatoes, onion, garlic, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Mix well.
Pour mixture over beans. Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs over bean mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: time saver chocolate cake
directions: Sift together in a bowl flour and sugar.
Bring to boil in a saucepan margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Pour over flour mixture.
Beat and add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and buttermilk which has soda added.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° until done to touch.
Just before cake is done, prepare frosting.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight or about 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed.
While hot, punch holes all over top with fork.
Pour the combined milk and cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool and cover with mixture of Cool Whip and frozen coconut.
(Save some coconut to sprinkle on top.) Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: steve's scratch chocolate fudge cake
directions: If using self-rising flour, decrease baking soda to 3/4 teaspoon and omit salt.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix well and let dough cool in refrigerator.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick and cut with floured cookie cutters.
Bake on cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost with buttercream frosting and decorate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter and then combine all ingredients, except French fried onion rings.
Pour mixture into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; then top with onion rings.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Store in airtight container.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat until smooth batter.
Stir in apples.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and top with Topping.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute onion and barley in butter until golden.
Take off heat. Stir in parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon into an ungreased casserole dish.
Before ready to cook, heat broth and stir in to blend.
Cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken and reserve broth. Skin, bone and cut chicken. Saute in butter (or margarine) the celery and diced onion.

title: lemon dill pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place rice in buttered baking dish; pour onion soup over rice. Lay chicken over this, spreading out so each piece will brown separately.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Melt cinnamon drops in water.
Pour over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce and cook until almost thick.
Fold in celery and pecans.
Store in refrigerator until set.

title: no bake cookies or preacher cookies
directions: Melt margarine. Add to margarine sugar, milk and cocoa. Boil for 2 minutes. Take off heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Stir 1 minute and drop by teaspoon on wax paper. You can add coconut, nuts or raisins, if desired.

title: kraft 100% parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Dip chicken in spread.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until tender.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, salt and corn syrup to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Place coated popcorn in 2 large buttered cake pans.
Bake at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes, for about an hour.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix together eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar and zucchini.
In a large bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Add zucchini mixture to dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes or longer, until bread tests done.

title: mexican pinto beans
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans and return to pot.
Add 5 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yields 7 cups.

title: summer turkey and vegetable bake(low-fat)
directions: To Microwave:
Arrange zucchini in 13 x 9-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave at High (100% power) 8 minutes or until tender, rotating dish halfway through cooking.
Drain zucchini slices on paper towels; cover with additional paper towels to absorb all liquid.

title: hearty vegetable barley soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add onion & garlic till onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Cover, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables.
Cook for 10 minutes until vegetables are done.
Additional water may be added if it becomes too thick upon standing.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix oleo, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture over graham cracker bottom.
Top with cherries.

title: scrambled eggs especial
directions: Mix eggs,
pepper,
salt
and cream with fork.	Stir in avocado.
Heat
margarine
in
12-inch
Dutch oven over medium heat until just
hot
enough
to sizzle a drop of water.
Pour egg mixture into oven.	As egg mixture begins to set at bottom and side,
lift
cooked
portion
with spatula so the thin uncooked portion
can
flow to the bottom.
Avoid constant stirring.
Cook until eggs are thickened through but still moist. Sprinkle bacon on eggs.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Arrange layers of
vegetables
in
bowl.
Sprinkle each with salt and pepper.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover	and
chill for several hours.
Gently lift vegetables to coat with dressing.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion. Add peppers, soups and enchilada sauce. Place a little sauce in the bottom of baking dish. Layer tortillas, sauce and cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used, usually 3 layers. Cover with tinfoil and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place in greased baking dish.
Mix 2 cups corn flakes (crushed) with 3 tablespoons butter.
Place on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini stuffed with cheese and onion
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash zucchini, then cut in half lengthwise.
Heat 1/2-inch water in large saucepan.
When it boils, add zucchini halves and simmer for about 3 minutes, just to soften them; then drain well.
Using a teaspoon, scoop out center of zucchini to leave a cavity for stuffing.
Chop up scooped-out zucchini.
Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion for 5 minutes, then add garlic and chopped zucchini.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat and stir in cheese, thyme and salt and pepper to taste.
Fill zucchini shells and bake in greased pan for 20 to 30 minutes.
Can be served with fresh tomato sauce.

title: slaw
directions: Sprinkle salt on top of grated cabbage.
Let stand for 1 hour. Drain.
Place sugar, vinegar and water in pot and simmer.
Add remaining ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix together and pour into casserole dish. Top with bacon slices. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon together in plastic bag. Grease an angel food pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Open one package of biscuits at a time, separate biscuits and cut into quarters. Shake a few at a time in plastic bag and place in pan.
Continue until all are used.
Sprinkle leftover sugar-cinnamon mixture over top.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat rest of ingredients except nuts.
Mix in nuts by hand and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: sour cream chicken nachos
directions: Combine sour cream, Cheez Whiz and picante in saucepan; stir over low heat until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Stir in chicken.
On serving platter, layer half of chips, Cheez Whiz mixture, lettuce, tomato and olives.
Repeat layers.
Top with additional sour cream (if desired).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake sweet potatoes for 1 hour at 400° or until done.
Cut in half lengthwise and cool slightly.
Scoop out potatoes into food processor; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon mixture into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp and refrigerate. Put shells in a pot with about two quarts of water and simmer for 30 minutes. Strain the peelings from the liquid. Reduce by half.
Congratulations! You have just made shrimp stock. Keep it hot on the back of the stove.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Note:
Can substitute fruits of choice (optional).

title: corn, crawfish and potato soup
directions: Saut butter and onions until tender. Add cream of potato soup and creamed corn; mix well. Cook for about 5 to 10 minutes over medium heat. Add crawfish, half and half and all spices, stirring until well blended. Cook 20 to 30 minutes over medium to low heat, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: devilite eggs
directions: Discard yolks.
Blend mayonnaise, Ricotta cheese, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Fill eggs.
Top as desired.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until blended.
Add ice water and mix well.
Allow to set.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk until smooth and thick.
Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Add jello and mix together until well blended.
Pour into pie shells and chill. Just before serving, place dollup of Cool Whip on each slice of pie and garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: peanut breakfast squares
directions: Combine peanut butter and honey until well blended.
Stir in dry powdered milk and add cereal until blended.
Press into 8 inch pan and chill 30 minutes.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: angel delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add ice cream and strawberries. Stir until ice cream melts. Chill until thickened, approximately 20 minutes. Spread strawberry mixture between layers of cake; chill 4 hours.
Before serving, frost cake with whipped topping.

title: zucchini caviar
directions: Shred zucchini and finely chop onion; saute with garlic, dill weed, thyme and oil until zucchini is tender.
Remove from heat. Finely chop tomatoes and add with lemon peel and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine with other ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Stir in lemon juice just before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: ham and swiss pie
directions: Put ham, cheese and onion in 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over ham mixture.
Bake until golden, 35 to 40 minutes.
A great brunch idea!

title: corn sticks
directions: Beat all together, adding melted lard last!
Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour batter into corn stick pan and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients for crust.
Press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sides should be 1 3/4 inches high.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise and pimento.
Refrigerate.

title: orange peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water.
Bring to a boil to thicken.
Add
jello and cool.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add corn and thawed broccoli and crumbs; leave 1 cup aside.
Put in casserole.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I like to pour about 1/2 to 3/4 cup catsup on top before baking.

title: apple chutney(indian condiment)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a pan over high heat.
Combine cider and brown sugar.
Add apple mixture and salt.
Simmer until reduced to 2 cups.
Cool.
Serve with ham or curried dishes.
Serves 10.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake about 30 minutes or until top is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: silly putty
directions: Let sit for 5 minutes, then knead and mix with hands.
Store in airtight container.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove from fat and crumble.
Add okra to bacon drippings; saute until soft.
Add bell pepper and onions; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon; cook until thick on low heat.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Soak raisins for several hours or overnight in pineapple and juice.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in jam.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately to cream mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Pour batter into floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: granny's ginger cakes(cookies)
directions: Mix to very soft dough.
Roll out and cut into blocks.
Do not have leftover dough for next turn to roll.
Dries out too much. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab salad from albertson's
directions: Separate crab meat with fork.
Mix other ingredients and place in refrigerator until serving time.

title: lo-cal meal
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute mixed vegetables in small amount of olive oil along with any other fresh vegetables you care to add.
If using fresh tomatoes, add just before serving.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix in cooked spaghetti and about 2 tablespoons sesame oil and teriyaki sauce.

title: rouladen(beef rolls)
directions: Pound meat slices with steak mallet.
Spread mustard thinly over meat.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, pickles, bacon and onions. Roll up and secure with skewers or string. Brown in butter.
Place in roaster with small amount of water. Cover and bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Make gravy with the broth and add sour cream before serving.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Boil 5 minutes raisins and water.
Add other ingredients and boil.
Make crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trash(sweet)
directions: In a large saucepan, melt together chocolate morsels and butter.
Stir in peanut butter until well mixed.
Let cool.
When cool, mix with other ingredients by hand.
Pour powdered sugar in a large brown paper bag.
Dump mixture in bag and shake, shake, shake (add more powdered sugar if needed).
Store in giant canister if it lasts that long.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix well, then turn out on a piece of waxed paper and roll into a rectangle about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with 1/2 cup of peanut butter (creamy or chunky style).
Roll up like jelly roll and chill for about 8 hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2 quart saucepan, melt butter. On a piece of waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil and garlic salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in crumbs to coat.
Place skin-side up in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
While chicken is baking, add wine, onion and parsley to remaining melted butter.
When chicken is brown, pour sauce over and around.
Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes more until sauce is hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients; roll in ball.
Refrigerate.
Roll in pecans and serve.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Let come to a bubbling boil.
Add crawfish and rice.
Cook 3 minutes. Pour into casserole, top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: popcorn cookies
directions: Place popcorn in a food processor or blender and process until moderately fine.
Combine with nuts and set aside.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Add bananas, nuts and spices.
Makes one loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sunday roast
directions: Layer with beans, roast, onion and seasonings and then pour tomato sauce on top.
Cover with water to 2 1/2 inches from the top of the roaster pan.
Bake at 250° for 12 hours in oven.
This may be cooked in a slow cooker.
Cook on low for approximately 12 to 18 hours.
Add a salad and bread and you have Sunday dinner.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients to a cream and Proverbs 23:14.
Add the next ingredient and repeat Proverbs 23:14.
Add the next 3 ingredients and repeat Proverbs 23:14.
Add the remaining ingredients except the last one, after mixing them together.
Add the last ingredient.
Leviticus 26:26 at 300° to 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Grind cranberries in blender.
In bowl, cover berries with sugar.
Let stand one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: grandma's hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine the margarine, cocoa, powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, then take off heat and add the vanilla.
Serve hot over vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1 cup of pecans.
Place one cup of pecans on a sheet of foil.
Put mixture on the spread nuts and press into ball of mixture.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice onions and squash together.
Cook down with water until tender.
Mix other ingredients except dressing mix.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with herb dressing mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sciple's corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in hot greased skillet at 400° until brown.

title: moms martin salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail and set aside. Mix boiling water and jello until dissolved.
Add softened cream cheese to hot jello mixture.
Gradually beat in 1 cup of the fruit juices.
Beat until foamy.
Chill until soft set.
Then add fruit and cool whip.
Mix well with beater.
Then fold in marshmallows. Chill overnight or for several hours.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, then add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms (with juice), chopped olives, soups and 1/2 soup can of water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles and melt cheeses.
Put meat mixture in large bowl and add all cheeses and pimentos.
Mix well.
Add noodles and mix until well blended. Place in casserole dish (with cover).
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In hot oil cook onion, garlic and cayenne pepper until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato juice and beans.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice; heat through.
Garnish with thyme, if desired.

title: heart healthy spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise to blend.
Stir in spinach, water chestnuts and green onions.
Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes. Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip. Layer pudding mix, bananas and wafers. End with pudding topped with wafers.

title: sweet lunch pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and peppers in layers with 1/2 cup salt.
Cover with ice; chill for 3 hours. Drain well.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to boil.
Add cucumber mixture; bring back to boil slowly.
Boil 1/2 hour with stirring (very low boil).
Pack in jars.
Makes 8 pints.
Good with soup beans.

title: fluffy apple salad
directions: Put pineapple chunks and marshmallows together in a bowl and stir occasionally.
The marshmallows soak up the liquid from the pineapple and will soften.

title: special cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch spring-form pan and line with wax paper.
Put cheese and eggs in blender.
Blend until no lumps are left.
Place in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Turn oven off but leave cake in oven for another hour.
Cool well to hold together.

title: peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, butter and salt.
Cut to resemble coarse crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Arrange peaches on crust.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Combine reserved peach syrup, evaporated milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 40 minutes or until set.

title: suppertime cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Melt butter in a skillet; saute onion and celery until tender.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients and add to carrots.
Let marinate several hours.
Serve cold.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut enough cucumbers, onions and peppers to pack a 1 gallon jar.
Heat syrup until it boils.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let cool and refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator for months.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a large enough casserole dish to accomodate the apples and to allow space at the top for the topping. Pour apples over bottom of casserole. Mix cinnamon and water; pour liquids over apples. Mix together dry ingredients and butter until crumbly. Put mixture over apples. Bake at 350° in oven for 40 to 60 minutes. Serve warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and you have a Taco Salad!
You may choose to replace the beans with cooked hamburger (drained).
I choose not to cook!

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings.
Roll wings in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in cooking oil.
Brown onions.
Mix brown sugar, catsup, mustard, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Add browned onions.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add browned wings in baking dish.
Pour sauce over wings.
Bake in oven at 325° for one hour.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into 8-inch cake pan.
Make 3 depressions in dry ingredients.
Pour vinegar into one, vanilla into another and oil in third.
Pour water over all.
Mix well until smooth. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.
Serve topped with vanilla ice cream, whipped cream or chocolate fudge sauce.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in hot oil until browned.
Add peppers; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add pineapple with juice, vinegar, sugar, ginger and garlic powder.
Bring to full boil.
Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refried beans
directions: Put cooking oil in skillet, let heat until hot.
Add pepper; saute.
Add beans, do not stir for a few minutes.
After beans have fried for a few minutes, press down on them as you stir, until most beans are mashed.
Remove from heat and top with cheese.

title: company fried chicken
directions: Rinse and dry each piece of chicken.
Mix oil and margarine. Place oil and margarine mixture in a large, high-sided cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
In a large plastic storage bag, mix flour, salt, paprika, white pepper and dried marjoram.
One at a time, dip chicken pieces in the oil mixture, then shake it in the flour mixture and place on a paper towel.
Repeat this process until all chicken is coated.
Place chicken pieces skin side up on cookie sheet containing any remaining oil mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn the chicken over and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook in boiling water until done (10 to 11 minutes); drain.
Add eggs, well beaten, and Parmesan to spaghetti.
Press into greased 10-inch pie pan; form up sides.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan, set aside.
Dilute soup with 1 full can milk.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan the potatoes, onions, soup, milk and last pork chops.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover for the last 15 minutes for browning.

title: apple crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Slice apples into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon.
Crumble sugar, flour and butter together.
Sprinkle the topping over the apples.
Sprinkle a little extra sugar over the top if you wish.
Bake for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with custard, ice cream or cream.

title: pork chops with apples and stuffing
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops in oil over medium-high heat.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Fold in chocolate bits. Pour cake mix in pan.
Evenly cover with cream cheese mixture. Bake about 45 to 55 minutes.
Cream cheese mixture will form a filling in the center of cake as it bakes.
May serve with whipped cream or just dust with confectioners sugar.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again. Add eggs and beat well. Stir in the molasses. Add dry ingredients alternately with hot water in which soda has been dissolved. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12 pan. Remove from pan. Cool. Cut in squares. Serve with whipped cream.

title: salami
directions: First day:
Mix well, cover and refrigerate.

title: roast and gravy with rice
directions: Flour roast and brown both sides.
Remove roast and make gravy.
Put roast back in deep covered skillet; cook until tender. Add onion, tomatoes and garlic.
Simmer for half hour.
Cook rice separate and serve with gravy and roast.

title: happy salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add sugar and cold water. Thicken slightly. Add pineapple, cranberries, celery, apple and nuts.
Pour into mold or serving dish.
Refrigerate until set. Serves 6.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat broth in saucepan.
Add potatoes, pepper and seasoned salt.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla and stir well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased 8-inch square baking pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
