Cool and cut into squares.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Does well with reduced-fat mayonnaise and sour cream.
Best done the day before. Use for raw vegetables.
Great also on baked potatoes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In a large stainless steel saucepan, mix together all ingredients.
Over medium heat, cook until the mixture thickens. Remember to stir because there is a possibility of scorching.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with chicken or turkey or your favorite cold roast meats.

title: crazy crust
directions: Mix shortening, egg, water and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour 1/2 mixture in pie pan.
Add filling.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Check with knife.
Makes 1 pie.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Next, spread blueberries over pineapple. Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar over blueberries. Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture. Melt butter and pour over cake mix. Top with chopped nuts and remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole supreme
directions: Peel and boil the potatoes until tender. Drain and beat in a large bowl until fluffy, adding butter, seasonings and milk. Check to see if it needs more seasonings.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch pan. Fold cheese into whipped cream and spread over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, only until golden brown.
Serves 10.

title: real lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until foamy.
Stir in 1 cup sugar into the yolks very gradually, beating constantly.
Now stir in the flour and salt until smooth, then pour in lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Add the boiling water last.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until the filling is smooth and thick. Takes about 20 minutes.
Cool before pouring into pie shell.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet; pour into colander and rinse well.
Put into slow cooker.
Add onions, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Stir until mixed well.
Salt and cover.
Cook on high for 4 hours.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Divide into 4 parts and color with food coloring.
Place in Tupperware Bell Tumblers or Snack Cups.
Great fun for the kids because they can eat it!

title: tangy lime punch
directions: Combine lime drink mix, lemonade, pineapple juice, water and lemon juice. Chill.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add beaten egg. Fold in cake mix.
Chill several hours.
Form balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Cook until edges are slightly brown.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and top with topping.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the above and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sausage patties
directions: Mix the oats, salt, sage and eggs.
Form into 4 flat patties. Fry in the butter until brown on both sides.
Boil 1 quart water. Add bouillon cube.
Pour over patties.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, approximately 45 minutes.
In microwave or a sprayed nonstick skillet, cook bell pepper and onion until tender.
Put this in a large mixing bowl and set aside. Cook the turkey sausage; drain.
Mix with the cooked vegetables.
Add the cheese to the hot mixture; stir until cheese is melted.
Add drained mushrooms, pimentos, soup and cooked rice.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° until hot, bubbly and slightly browned.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream the oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour, cocoa and buttermilk alternately.
Boil water and soda together and add last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.
(Use a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.)

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
With pastry blender, cut in butter and half of the cheese until coarse and crumbly.
Add ice water.
Shape into a ball.
Roll out pastry 1/8 inch thick. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Fold dough in half and roll out 1/8 inch thick again.
Cut pastry into 5 inches long and about 1/2 inch wide.
Sprinkle with celery seed.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all except chocolate chips thoroughly then beat for about 4 minutes by hand.
Add chocolate chips and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan for 50 to 60 minutes, until firm.
Chocolate chips do not melt but remain suspended throughout the cake.

title: quiche
directions: Fry crumbled sausage and onion until browned.
Cook broccoli, then drain.
Beat together eggs, milk, pepper and mix.
Put sausage, onion, broccoli and cheese in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: nana's brownies(yield: depends on how you cut them.)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: no-knead french bread
directions: Note:
As you see, I put down to use Robin Hood flour.
That's because it is the best brand to use in making breads and rolls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cooled mashed sweet potatoes with sugars in mixer bowl until smooth.
Add butter, a few pieces at a time, beating until melted.
Beat in salt, nutmeg and pumpkin pie spice.
Gradually add milk and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into pie crust.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Mix and wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill.
Roll into ball, then roll in cheese.

title: fettucini and spinach
directions: In large skillet, cook spinach and garlic in oil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add bouillon mixture, basil, cottage cheese and salt to spinach.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Toss spinach mixture, grated cheese and noodles.
Serve in heated dish, garnished with parsley. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Cool.
Mix sugar, soup, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring this mixture to a boil (until sugar is dissolved).
Pour over carrots, onions and green pepper. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag (or bowl). Moisten potatoes in milk and coat well with dry mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once after first 30 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with parsley.

title: pork sausage
directions: Grind meat fine in food chopper.
Sprinkle spices over meat and mix well.
Refrigerate, freeze, sack or can.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Press crescent roll triangles together in ungreased 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Press up the sides 1/2-inch or more.
Spread crust with Dijon mustard.

title: lobster or crab bisque
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a pan.
Cook slowly until onion is yellow.
Add lobster.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and tomato paste/paprika.
Add broth.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove parsley.
Add cream/milk.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with salt and cayenne pepper.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken for 30 minutes or until tender.
Cool and remove from bones.
Place chicken in lightly buttered casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Toss crumbs with butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: golden nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in egg well. Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to first mixture alternately with undiluted orange juice concentrate, stirring after each addition.
Quickly stir in nuts and pineapple (do not drain).
Bake in greased small loaf pan (approximately 9 x 5 x 3-inch) in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Empty onto rack to cool.

title: bobby's cheesy chicken rolls
directions: Warm soup with milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix chicken with 1 cup cheese.
Fill 8 rolls with chicken mixture and roll up, seam side down in glass baking dish.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons soup mixture over each roll.
(You can pour all of mixture over rolls if you wish.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with remaining soup mixture as gravy.

title: chile cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil; add grits and salt.
Cook over low heat 2 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add butter and cheese; stir until melted.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in eggs; add chiles.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain. Brown ground beef in large pot. Add all other ingredients, including pasta. Mix well and place in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until browned as desired.

title: orange crinkles cookies
directions: Note:
Different flavors cake mix can be used.

title: pineapple carrot slaw
directions: Cut pineapple into chunks.
Combine cabbage, carrots and pineapple chunks.
Mix together mayonnaise and dill weed until well blended.
Toss with salad.
Makes 2 servings.

title: ham rings
directions: Take tortillas, ham, cheese and layer spinach dip last.
Roll up tightly in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
To use, cut into 1/8-inch slices.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in grapes.
Put in 9 x 13 serving piece and top with brown sugar and nuts.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cut onions into 1/2-inch slices. Caramelize in stick of butter on stove top. Add all other ingredients except bouillon water; mix well. Add bouillon water and bring to a boil. Turn down and simmer 1 to 2 hours. Toast French bread slices on both sides. Put soup in bowls; top with bread slice. Lay Mozzarella slice on top and place in broiler until cheese has melted.

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Cook sausage and crumble; drain well.
Mix other ingredients with sausage.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry pie filling
directions: Prepare usual pie crust.
Dissolve jello with boiling water and add to heated cherries.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cook egg, sugar, flour and vinegar until thick.
When cool, combine with whipped cream and toss together with bananas, grapes, oranges and pecans.

title: gourmet oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt, if desired, in separate bowl.
Add to margarine mixture; mix well.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before removing to racks to cool.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash, string and cut celery into 2 to 3-inch pieces in mixing bowl.
Combine pimento, cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Stuff mixture into the celery pieces.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together everything but cheese.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk. Pour into a greased 9-inch baking dish.
Top with Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions. While cake is hot, poke holes in top of cake, pour milk and caramel topping over cake. Let cool. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed butterfingers.

title: four layer supper dish
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet, stirring to break up meat. Drain off fat.
Wash potatoes and cut into slices (do not peel). Place sliced potatoes in a large baking pan or casserole.
Spoon the green beans on top, then the ground beef and finally the cheese.
Pour the milk over all.
Cover and cook over low heat or bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: stroganoff steak sandwich
directions: In a shallow dish, combine beer, oil, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Marinate steak, covered, overnight in refrigerator or several hours at room temperature.
Drain.
Broil steak 3-inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes on each side for medium rare.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise, just scrub and rinse them.
Cut into thin slices, using the handle of a spoon to cradle potato so you do not cut all the way through.
Fan potatoes out slightly and put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, butter and herbs.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Use leftover roast beef.
Cut into bite size pieces; add water, leftover gravy, cubed potatoes and chopped onions.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling into lightly greased casserole.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and oats until crumbly; sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: julia mae's pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla and nuts, in large saucepan and cook on medium heat until a path forms on bottom of pot.
Add vanilla and toasted or untoasted nuts.
Remove from heat, whip well, then drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side up, in shallow baking pan.
Pour preserve mix on chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until fork can be inserted with ease, basting occasionally with the pan drippings. Serve hot with plain rice and sweet and sour sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: roasted garlic and parmesan mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small ovenproof cup or bowl, combine garlic and olive oil.
Cover and bake about 25 minutes or until garlic is very soft.
Leaving oven on at 350°
to bake potatoes later, remove garlic from oven and let cool.
Mash with fork, reserving oil.
While garlic is roasting, place potatoes in a pot and cover with water.
Add salt and bring to a boil.
Let cook until tender.
Drain potatoes and place in large bowl.
Add half and half, sour cream, butter, mashed garlic and half of reserved olive oil to potatoes.

title: stewed chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chickens in a large kettle with enough water to cover. Cover with lid and bring to a boil.
Skim off residue that rises to surface.
Add remaining ingredients, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to an hour or until the meat is tender.
(Simmer - do not boil.)
Drop in dumplings and cook 15 minutes.

title: mushroom caviar
directions: Cook onions until soft.
Add mushrooms, coriander, salt and pepper.
Cook until mushrooms let off their juice.
Turn up heat and cook until most of liquid evaporates.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Add seasoning, if necessary.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with thinly sliced black bread.
Freezes well.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add baking powder to flour.
Mix all together.
Pour into 4 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Set inside pan of water.
Bake in slow oven about 45 minutes.
This raises and falls and is doughy when done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Puree 1/3 peppers and vinegar at a time in a blender.
Add salt, sugar and mustard to puree mixture and bring to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mix flour and water to a paste mixture and add to mixture while it is at a boil.
To make hotter, add hot pepper seeds.
The more seeds the hotter it is. Put in sterilized canning jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Pound beef slices to flatten and tenderize.
Mix egg and 1 tablespoon milk in pie pan. Dip meat in egg mixture, then in crushed crackers.
In a heavy skillet, brown meat in hot oil. When meat is browned, season with salt and pepper.
Cover skillet. Reduce heat and simmer slowly about 45 to 60 minutes or until tender. Remove meat to platter and keep warm.

title: easy mexican layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in shallow serving dish in order listed. Chill and serve with tortilla chips.
You can also add seasoned ground beef, onions, guacamole, etc. as desired.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in microwave.
Blend in sugar, eggs and nuts.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable strudel
directions: Cut carrots and red pepper into matchstick strips.
Dice onions and mushrooms; coarsely slice escarole.

title: sweet potatoes with peaches
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes and peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the juice from the peaches.
Sprinkle the cinnamon and brown sugar over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir the mixture and continue baking 15 to 25 minutes more, until there is a coating over the potatoes.

title: rouladen(beef roll-ups)
directions: Pound steaks until they are 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Salt, pepper and season with paprika.
Put 1 slice of bacon and chopped onions on each steak and roll up. Secure with a toothpick.
Fry in oil or butter, then add 2 cups water and bouillon.
Let cook 2 hours. This is very good served with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix milk, pudding and whipped topping.
Break up Oreos and put in food processor or blender until crushed very fine.
Layer cake in a foil or plastic lined flower pot.
Put 1/3 of crushed cookies in bottom of container.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with 1/3 cookies, then remaining filling.
Top with rest of cookie crumbs before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together, put in crock pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: simple fudge
directions: Melt snaps.
Add sweetened condensed milk all at once.
Stir quickly.
Mix coating and milk thoroughly.
Do not overmix. Overmixing causes oils to separate from fudge.
Take fudge mixture off bottom of bowl and mix in the nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan lined with wax paper.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; put 1 layer in bottom of dish.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and Cool Whip.
Add on top of cookies; add one more layer of cookies.
Chill and eat.
May garnish with gummy worms.
Kids love 'em!

title: zesty barbecued ribs
directions: In large pan, cook ribs in boiling water 45 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Grill or broil ribs as desired, turning and basting frequently with sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy divinity
directions: Cook sugar and water until mixture forms a ball in water.
Add Marshmallow Creme and chopped nuts.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat 2 cups of water and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Add remaining cup of cold water.
Add sugar.
Grind cranberries and orange.
Add all together with celery.
Mix and let stand in dish until firm.

title: whole wheat pastry
directions: Mix just
as for Plain Pastry except resift the 2 kinds of flour
and
salt
together.
Stir
the
bran
back into the sifted mixture.
Makes 1 double crust or 2 single pie crusts.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, water and salt.
Add milk.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: With mixer, blend softened cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in peanut butter and Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into lightly greased round pan.
Bake 25 - 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together and put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
(Bake in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.)

title: sweet cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in bowls.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and chill for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Get a medium-size pot.
Pour in your 2 1/2 cups of water; bring to a rolling boil.
Pour in macaroni and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir until macaroni becomes soft and tender.
Pour in saucepan and mix in cheese.

title: squash casserole 5
directions: Mix squash, onion and melted margarine.
Add stuffing mix, milk and cheese.
Combine until well mixed.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel and slice 1 potato per each person.
Use 1 medium onion for every 2 potatoes, sliced.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut butter or margarine over top, 2 teaspoons per potato.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Cover; microwave on High until tender, 8 to 14 minutes, depending on amount.
Stir halfway through cooking time. Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.

title: oriental pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse with cold water, drain and chill.
Steam asparagus 6 minutes until crisp-tender.

title: sausage delights
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Form into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Press into patties.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: betty's ham glaze(recipe for 8 pound ham)
directions: Score and stick with cloves and place in aluminum foil.
Bake in 300° oven.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg.
Cream until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth and blend in 2 tablespoons milk.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Dredge cut-up chicken in flour and brown. Remove chicken. Cook onion in oil until golden. Add salt and pepper. Simmer slowly until tender. Add broth or water as needed. When chicken is tender, remove to dish.
Add sour cream to broth and pour over chicken.

title: butterball coffee cake
directions: Separate
and
halve biscuits.
Dip each piece in melted butter, then roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place biscuits in greased
round
layer
pan,
overlapping
each piece.
Pour any leftover butter
on
top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Start layers beginning with graham cracker crumb mixture, then add other layers as follows:
coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, condensed milk, nuts.
Press down gently as you add layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients with sour cream.
Top with a small portion of the coconut.
Garnish with cherry on top.
Tastes best when chilled in refrigerator for a couple of hours before serving.

title: goulash
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until onion is tender; drain off fat.
Add macaroni, salt, chili powder, sugar, black pepper and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Combine tomato paste and 1/4 cup water; add to pan and cook an additional 10 minutes, or until done.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over first layer.
Mix pudding as directed on package and spread on second layers.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed pecans.
(Graham cracker crust can be used for first layer.)

title: stacked enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in skillet, then add tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic powder and onion.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly. Place 2 tortillas in sauce, turning once and removing with large spatula as soon as tortilla is softened.
Place on plate, topping each with Velveeta.
Continue to layer tortillas and cheese onto plate until you build a stack.
Top again with cheese.
Salt to taste.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: iced mocha
directions: Combine all ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.
Pour over ice and serve.

title: valentine sugar cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and extracts.
Stir in flour.
Mix well.
Chill several hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2 or 3-inch heart shaped cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased bakings sheets.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix in a bowl and beat together well eggs, oil and sugar. Add cut up apples. Sift together rest of ingredients; add to apple mix.

title: jackie's very chocolate cheesecake
directions: In the top of a double boiler over simmering water melt the butter and chocolate.
Add the water and vanilla and stir until blended.
Add the sugar and whisk until smooth.
Pour over the cooled cheesecake.
Garnish with the strawberries.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, and stir well.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: double decker pastry
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and soda and salt. Add shortening.
Add egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend until dough forms.
Divide into 3 portions.
Roll between waxed paper as for jelly roll.
Remove paper.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Place chocolate morsels in a 4 cup glass measure.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) 2 1/2 minutes or until melted when stirred. Add peanut butter; microwave on High 30 seconds, or until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet lined with wax or parchment paper.
Chill until set.
Store between sheets of wax paper in closed container at room temperature.
Makes 20 pieces.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns.
Toss gently to coat. Spoon about 1/3 cup on bottom of each hamburger bun; cover with bun tops.
Wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Put butter and onions in pan and saute.
Add mushroom soup and water and simmer a few minutes.
In a casserole dish, put rice, Cheez Whiz and broccoli.
Mix and add soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sauteed tofu and vegetables
directions: Cut up vegetables.
In large skillet saute onion until tender. Add carrots and cook a few minutes.
Add broccoli.
Cut tofu into small cubes and add to vegetables.
Press garlic into mix.
Stir well and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Put all in bowl and whip until thick for 10 minutes.
Spread on cake.
Can use other flavored pudding mix.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: This is great for a large group, served with ham.
Prepare in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, cool slightly- peel and dice.
Add salt, onion, and French dressing and marinate.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix carefully.
(More mayonnaise may be added.)
Serves 50. Refrigerate well.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13x9 pan in oven. Heat sweetened fruit and water in saucepan.
In the meantime, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in milk and beat until smooth.
Pour over margarine and top with fruit mixture. Bake at 375 degrees about 30 - 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out onto a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing together.
Spread onto crescent rolls.
Top with diced or shredded carrots, broccoli, cauliflower, celery, cucumber, tomatoes, peppers, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: doris bell's taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add beans and seasoning mix to meat mixture.
Add 2/3 can tomato sauce to make pudding consistency.
Simmer on very low heat for 5 minutes.
Pour into an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Layer the following in order: sour cream, lettuce (thin layer), tomato, Cheddar cheese and corn chips.

title: pot of potatoes
directions: In lightly greased casserole dish, layer potatoes, ground beef, onion, mushroom soup and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Combine ingredients in punch bowl.
Mix in 4 cups cold water.

title: spicy pepper steak
directions: Heat wok or 12 inch skillet over high heat. Add oil; rotate wok to coat side. Add beef; stir fry about 2 minutes or until brown. Add bell pepper and onion; stir fry about 1 minute or until vegetables are crisp tender. Stir in hoisin sauce; cook and stir about 30 seconds or until hot. Serve with noodles. This has 9 grams carbohydrates.

title: seafood dip
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor and chop fine. Add enough mayonnaise to moisten. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Stew potatoes in jackets.
Skin and mash.
Add butter, sugar, milk, orange juice, rind and eggs.
Put in buttered casserole. Sprinkle buttered nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix apples, celery, marshmallows and pecans together and add mayonnaise. Stir well and chill before serving.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mash 1/2 cup pecans into the bottom of thawed pie crusts. Brown pie crusts and let cool.
Mix with electric mixer at low speed the sugar, Cool Whip, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Spread half of this into each pie crust and top with blueberry pie filling.
Sprinkle rest of nuts on top.
Keep refrigerated.
Can be frozen for extended time if well covered.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir sliced zucchini and chopped onion in oleo for 10 minutes, then stir in parsley, salt and pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine beaten eggs and cheese.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch glass pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until center is set.
Cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: diabetic raisin bars
directions: Boil water and raisins until water is gone; let cool.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil; mix together.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Spoon into greased 11 x 17-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake longer if pan is smaller.
When cool, cut in bars.

title: fresh fried garden vegetables
directions: Chop up potatoes, hot peppers, sweet peppers, onions, red tomatoes and green tomatoes.
Mix together and put in skillet with 1 tablespoon of cooking oil.
sprinkle on garlic powder, salt and pepper.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally into thin slices 2-inches long.
Cook beef with pepper and onion.
Add celery and bouillon; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Combine cornstarch, water and soy sauce; blend until smooth and slowly add to skillet.
Stir until liquid is thickened, approximately 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat milk and pudding mix; blend in whipped topping and sweetened condensed milk.

title: sugarless punch
directions: Freeze juices, mixed together.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add Sprite and make slushy.
(You'll not miss the extra sugar!)

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes until thickened, stirring as needed. Cool mixture.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken pieces in a shallow baking pan, skin side up.
Combine butter, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder and mix well.
Pour over chicken and bake 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and nicely browned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with small amount of water until done. Drain well. Mix with other ingredients, except crackers. Pour mixture into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle crackers on the top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Add flour, soda and salt. Fold in fruit cocktail. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients; divide in half.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Let sit 8 hours (in refrigerator).
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: homemade salsa
directions: In a food processor, process onions, jalapenos, lemon juice, lime juice and cilantro.
Add drained tomatoes and pulse.
Add seasonings; mix by hand.
A good gift idea.

title: banana nut bread
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit the baking powder, salt and soda.

title: french bread
directions: Mix well.
Spread on bread.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven.

title: barbecued spanish ribs
directions: Bake at 325°.
Place meat in shallow pan.
In a bowl, combine salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, paprika, chili powder, catsup, water and vinegar.
Pour over meat.
Top with onion slices.
Bake for 1 hour, turn meat then continue baking 1 hour longer.
Baste meat occasionally with sauce while baking.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo; place layer of crackers on bottom of pan.
Mix pudding with milk and stir until it thickens, then mix in Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mixture over first layer of crackers, then add another layer of crackers, then rest of pudding.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate overnight, then put on a layer of chocolate icing.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Good for when you need to make ahead of time.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small pieces.
This will take approximately 3 months, so it is necessary to save the trunk for storage of cut pieces.
Add gravy to cover elephant.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer over slow fire for 27 days, until tender.
This stew serves 3,800 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits.
Add rabbits only if necessary, as no one likes to find hare in his stew!

title: lemon-lime salad mold
directions: Combine lime and lemon gelatin; dissolve in boiling water. Cool.
Stir in evaporated milk and lemon juice; chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts or celery.
Pour into a 2-quart mold or 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) square pans.
Chill until firm.
Yields 12 to 16 portions.
Serve with Mayonnaise Topping.

title: chicken gravy
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat. Whisk in flour and cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute. Whisk in broth, minced onion, milk and pepper. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, 2 minutes or until mixture thickens.

title: make-ahead breakfast bake
directions: In a large skillet, crumble the sausage and cook over medium heat until done. Drain on paper towels. Set aside.
Slice the crusts off the bread and cut into cubes.
Spread in the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with sausage and cheese. Set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine the eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over cheese and sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: ham and cheese melts
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions, mustard and poppy seed.
Split rolls and spread mixture on both sides.
Place ham and cheese on bottom half and replace the top; wrap in foil.
Heat at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello together.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix fruit in with jello and cottage cheese.
Stir the Cool Whip in.
(Can be made with pineapple jello.)

title: easy sunday dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix with the sugar, oil, 1 cup warm water and eggs.
Add the salt and flour. Stir well. Cover and let stand 6 to 8 hours.
Divide dough into 3 parts. Roll out as for pie crust.
(Brush with oleo or butter flavored Pam.)
Cut each pie into 8 wedges.
Roll up and let rise on greased baking sheet 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: mother's corn pudding
directions: Mix Crisco, flour and milk to make a white sauce.
Mix in all remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and cook in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Sift the next 4 ingredients and mix with the previous ingredients.
Dice apples and walnuts; mix all together.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar; remove from pans. Wrap in foil while hot.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly brush bread with dressing; place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top each pita with 2 process cheese food slices and desired pizza toppers.
Drizzle with additional dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes or until process cheese food begins to melt.
Cut into quarters.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: apricot cooler
directions: Combine juices and chill.
Add mineral water and ice (if desired) just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: five star kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, melted butter and vanilla and mix well.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a deep dish unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until center is done.

title: child rearing
directions: Combine all ingredients; add a pound of persistence and one cup of love. Whip until right consistency.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Melt and cool butter and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add the remaining ingredients (except corn); let cook 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole; add corn.

title: waffles
directions: Make a
hole in the sifted ingredients.
Pour in liquid. Combine with a few strokes.
The batter should have a pebbled look.
Fold in 3 egg whites, beaten stiff, last.

title: christmas custard
directions: Combine pudding, Dream Whip and sugar.
Slowly add milk.
Mix well.
Place in blender or using a mixer, beat until lightly fluffy.
You may add more milk to thin dow mixture.
Top with whipped topping.

title: kahlua
directions: Add water and coffee in a large pan.
Bring to a boil and add sugar. Stir and bring to a boil again.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool completely, then add vanilla and vodka.
Put in containers and let sit for 5 weeks.

title: deviled ground beef on mashed potatoes
directions: In large skillet, cook beef and onion until lightly browned. Drain fat off.
Sprinkle with flour, salt, mustard and pepper. Stir in water, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: mexican grilled chicken and rice
directions: Grill chicken breast. Prepare rice as directed. Add vegetables. Saut mushrooms and onions. Serve by placing chicken breasts over rice on plate. Mushrooms and onions over chicken. Cover with melted cheese. Serves 4.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix milk, pineapple, nuts, Cool Whip and lemon juice; mix well.
Divide mixture into the 2 pie crusts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mama's summer tomato pie
directions: Bake empty pie shell at 350° for 5 - 6 minutes, do not brown. Combine tomatoes, salt, basil, lemon pepper, and place in pie shell.
Mix Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise and spoon over tomatoes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Be sure to cook rice in 2 cups water according to directions.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Broccoli can be thawed so it can be broken up.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, then melted butter.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Grease pan well and drop 1 teaspoonful of mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: muskrat meat loaf
directions: Combine butter, onion salt, thyme and parsley.
In a cup measure or bowl (glass), microwave on High (100%) for 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: three layer cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until top is springy when gently touched.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars and beat.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: french salad
directions: Line bowl with graham cracker crumbs. Mix butter, powdered sugar and eggs together. Pour over graham cracker crumbs. Mix whipped cream, pineapple, nuts and vanilla together. Pour on top. Save some graham cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top. Make the day before and refrigerate.

title: potato-broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Add cream cheese, Swiss cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Add potatoes and stir well.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add Ro-Tel and refried beans; mix well. Place in a baking dish and top with cheese.
Place in oven at 400° to 450° for about 20 minutes.
Serve piping hot with chips.

title: frozen chocolate banana
directions: Put chopped peanuts into shallow bowl.
Put a piece of waxed paper on a plate.
Put chocolate pieces into skillet.
Put skillet on burner.
Turn burner to low heat.
Stir with wooden spoon until chocolate melts.
Remove skillet from heat.
Peel banana.
Cut in half.
Put a wooden stick into cut end of each banana half.
Spread chocolate on all sides of banana and roll in peanuts.
Put bananas on waxed-paper lined plate.
Freeze until hard.
Makes 2 servings.

title: marty's pork cutlets dijon
directions: Pat dry the cutlets.
Spread with mustard and dunk in bread crumbs, patting the crumbs on the cutlets to form a nice paste. Fry in hot oil until nicely browned; turn and brown the other side.
Cover frying pan and cook on medium-low heat for 30 to 40 minutes until pork is no longer pink.

title: buffet supper casserole
directions: Half cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Cool chicken.
Reserve broth. Remove meat in large pieces.
Skim broth.
You will need about 4 cups chicken pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix bread or cracker crumbs with butter. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Combine milk and cocoa in saucepan. Beat well. Add oleo, sweetener and salt. Bring to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients except 1/4 cup graham crackers. Cool about 15 minutes. Divide mixture into 32 balls. Roll in remaining cracker crumbs and chill.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind the first 7 ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup salt and a little salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Add the vinegar; cook for 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix.
Cook well, stirring continually.
Put into jars and seal.
Put in salad dressing if you want to before eating.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2-1/2 cups.
This is a good sauce to serve with boiled shrimp for a cocktail party or on a shrimp salad.

title: mom's doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Scald milk, then put in mashed potatoes and potato water.
Put potatoes through ricer, then eggs and sugar, then yeast and flour to stiffen.
Knead, then put in greased pan until doubled.
Roll out and cut.
Put on floured cloth and cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cake:
Mix first three ingredients together and press into oblong pan.

title: shrimp and scallops with capers
directions: Spray a flat casserole and lid with vegetable spray.
Put in all ingredients.
Drizzle with olive oil and toss.
Bake, covered, for 7 minutes at 400°.
Remove, toss and return to oven for 7 more minutes.
Remove, toss and return to oven for about 5 more minutes.
Serve on saffron rice with a nice Caesar salad and some good French bread-yum! Serves 2.
Recipe is easily doubled or tripled, but cooking time has to be adjusted, of course.

title: bear chili
directions: Cut bear meat into bite size pieces.
Brown in oil.
Add 2 cups of water and other ingredients except flour and beans. Bring to boil and simmer slowly 2 1/2 hours.
Stir in flour and beans.
Simmer 20 minutes longer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain beans and combine all ingredients except cheese and onions.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with onions.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in milk and rum extract.
Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form into 3 rolls, each about 10-inches long. Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight. Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, starting with sugar and corn meal.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into one 9-inch pie shell. Bake 45 minutes or until firm at 350°.

title: simple turnip greens
directions: Remove and discard stems and discolored spots from turnip greens. Tear into pieces, and set aside.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all the water is boiled out.
Add the applesauce, sweetener, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend in the flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour the mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.
(I use 3 small deep pans.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in greased baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix together sifted flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add unbeaten egg and mix with fork until crumbly.
Empty bowl on top of apples.
Drizzle melted butter over top evenly.
Top with cinnamon.

title: best-ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Beat together butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until blended.
Fold in oats and chocolate chips. Cover with plastic wrap; chill for 1 hour.

title: crushed strawberries for ice cream topping
directions: Crush and let stand about three days.
Stir several times a day.
They will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour and salt; cut in half of shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Cut in remaining shortening until mixture is consistency of small peas. Sprinkle water over mixture and stir gently with a fork until mixture holds together.
Press into a smooth ball.
Divide dough in thirds.
On lightly floured board or pastry cloth, roll out one-third of dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into small pieces, about 1 x 3-inches.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Cover remaining dough and continue with filling directions.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a lightly greased or sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan, layer rice, broccoli, chicken, cheese and mushrooms. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, soup, mustard and curry powder.
Pour over the chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Saute croutons or cracker crumbs in butter and sprinkle over the cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: cookie burgers
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, butter, milk and yellow and red food coloring to make a cheese-colored icing.
Tint the coconut with the green coloring.
Layer each burger in this order:
1 Nilla wafer, a dab of orange frosting, 1/2 Oreo (that's 2 chocolate cookie outside), a layer of orange frosting, a sprinkle of coconut and another Nilla wafer.
These cookie treats look like miniature cheeseburgers with lettuce.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin. Dissolve completely. Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch
pan. Chill at least 3 hours. Jigglers will be firm after 1 hour, but may be difficult to remove from pan.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together peanuts, sugar and syrup; cook on High 4 minutes. Stir; cook 4 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour into buttered pan or a sheet of aluminum foil.
Cool; break in pieces.
Microwave time:
9 minutes.
Cookware 1 1/2-quart microwave dish.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: mother's beef stew
directions: Brown beef with 2 teaspoons oil in skillet. Sprinkle beef with paprika. Boil vegetables until tender and add salt. Add flour to beef when brown and tender. Add beef to vegetables. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Delicious.

title: reuben roll-ups
directions: Roll dough into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle. Cut into eight 3 x 4 1/2-inch rectangles. Combine sauerkraut and salad dressing. Place a slice of beef on each rectangle. Top with about 2 tablespoons of sauerkraut mixture and a slice of cheese. Roll up. Place with seam side down on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden. Yield: 8 roll-ups.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine the buttermilk, eggs and oil. Pour into the dry ingredients, mixing only until dry ingredients are dampened.
Gently fold in berries.
(Frozen ones work great.) Spoon into greased muffin tin filling 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and white sugar in plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put biscuits in bag.
Shake to coat.
Put biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Put on a plate and pull apart to eat.
Best when warm!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease a baking sheet heavily.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart casserole.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave at High until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy.
Quickly spread on a greased baking sheet.
Spread as thin as possible for brittle candy.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Combine preserves, dressing and soup mix.
Spread over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 370°.
Turn and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: layered pumpkin dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Mix well, add nuts, and spread on bottom of
9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot chiffon pie
directions: Wash apricots and cover with water. Simmer 40 minutes or until all water is evaporated.
Beat until smooth; cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add cream and apricots.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until firm. Cool.
Top with whip cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set both cheeses out of the refrigerator until at room temperature, then mix the cheese, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce and minced garlic together until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then roll into 1 ball or 2 logs and then roll in the nuts until well coated.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in pie crust.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in bacon grease.
Add tomato puree, olives, crumbled bacon, garlic and bay leaves.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Cook noodles until almost done.
In a casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar and Karo syrup.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Add baking soda and stir quickly.
(Mixture will become white and frothy.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and cheese, then meat and onions.
Mix well.
Cook 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Bake in a 10-inch baking dish.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken in flour, salt, and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Put in pan (13 x 9-inch) for baking.
Brown onion, celery, and peppers in oil.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, water, and wine in pan.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken in pan.
Cover with foil. Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: pork and beans
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Add pork and beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
When sugar is melted, pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon strips and bake until bacon is crisp.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except m&m's, until will blended.
Add m&m's mix well.
Drop by teaspoon or ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-20 minutes.

title: soup from leftover turkey
directions: Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Fold in sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold gently into creamed mixture, stirring just to blend.
Mix together the nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of it in a well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Add rest of batter; sprinkle remaining cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let stand in pan or rack for 5 minutes.
Loosen around edges and turn out on plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in butter or margarine until tender, about 15 minutes, covered.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter thoroughly and add sugar gradually until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk until blended on low speed.
Add flavoring and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until straw comes out clean.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream butter, sugar and add eggs.
Alternate bananas and flour.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Store in jar.
Use 3 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add 1 tablespoon granulated sugar.
Beat eggs; add 1/2 cup granulated sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add melted margarine to yeast mixture; add in egg mixture. Stir in flour; chill for approximately 7 hours or overnight.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness as for a pie.
Slice in triangular pieces.
Roll dough starting with the larger end.
Let rise 4 hours in warm place.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in an oven set at 350°.

title: granny's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cocoa in a large saucepan.
Add stick of margarine and stir over low heat until margarine has melted.

title: lenten tuna casserole
directions: Fry onion in hot oil until soft. Add rice, tuna, soup and seasoning. Mix all together.
Pour into casserole.
Place pepper rings on top and bake about 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs.
Add milk, vinegar, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp and cream appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on bottom of serving dish.
Drain the shrimp.
Sprinkle lemon juice on shrimp.
Mix with the Heinz chile sauce, horseradish and Tabasco.
Spread on top of shrimp.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and chop vegetables.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, cheese and olives.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
(I usually put the cheese in last!)
Makes a bunch.

title: pam's rolls
directions: Scald milk with butter or margarine; cool to warm, but not real hot.
Add to sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in 2 cups of flour. Add beaten egg, then remaining flour.
Form into a ball on floured surface and knead until it forms a ball.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Save 2 tablespoons liquid.
Combine oranges, strawberries, bananas and marshmallows with liquid.
Mix lightly. Cover.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Chop strawberries in blender. Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water. Add strawberries and pineapples. Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan, when set, spread with cool whip. Makes 8 serving, each just about 22 calories.

title: willi's coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with a dash of salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut and vanilla.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325°
for about 20 minutes. Makes about 18 cookies.

title: top of stove supper
directions: Melt butter in a large, heavy skillet.
Layer next 6 ingredients in skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes. Pour eggs over ham mixture; cook an additional 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: open house punch(makes 32 four ounce drinks)
directions: Mix in punch bowl, adding 7-Up last. Add drops of red food coloring as desired (optional). Add ice cubes or block ice. Garnish with slices of lemon and orange.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons per mug of hot water.

title: patio beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan. Saute onion in bacon grease. In a large casserole, combine beans, cheese, sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Add onion and crumbled bacon. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones.
Cut into small pieces and put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: deluxe bars
directions: Cook together the brown sugar, milk, butter and graham cracker crumbs for 7 minutes; remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of Club soda crackers.
Put 1/2 filling on crackers, then another layer of Club crackers.
Add the rest of filling.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top all with melted butter and chips.
Cool overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook until clear.
Stir in Jell-O. Cool slightly.
Add strawberries.
Pour in pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: mama's barbecue sauce
directions: Add all ingredients together, bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: steamed vegetable medley
directions: In a large saucepan, steam broccoli and carrots over boiling water for about 6 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Add water chestnuts and tomatoes.
Steam about 1 minute, or until heated through.
Immediately remove from pan.
Place in serving bowl. Combine soy sauce and vinegar; drizzle over vegetables.
Gently toss to combine.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel, apple salad
directions: Mix cool whip, dry pudding mix, and pineapple.
Add peanuts, apples and marshmallows.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sugar, egg and butter, then stir in all dry ingredients together.
Add the milk and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: In skillet, combine first 5 ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Cook and stir until boiling.
Stir in potatoes and franks; heat through.
Top with snipped parsley, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: sauteed squash
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Pour olive oil in skillet or wok; heat.
Add onion and squash. Saute until tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions. Drain. Add remaining ingredients reserving 1 cup cheese and add egg last after mixture has cooled a little. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Add the cup of cheese the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: apricot bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed. Pour batter in a greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip. Put in crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked bacon and eggs
directions: Pan broil bacon until about half done.
Line muffin rings with bacon (sides and bottom).
Break egg into each cup and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 325° oven until desired doneness.

title: smoothie strawberry popsicles
directions: Combine fruit in container of food processor or blender; process until smooth.
Combine fruit juice and stir well.

title: salsa cruda dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and let stand 2 hours to blend flavors.
This is excellent with tortilla chips or can be used as a condiment with meat.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all together with a fork.
Shrimp will crumble when mashed with fork.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Add cocoa and salt to melted Crisco.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Put all sugar in a bowl.
Add chocolate mixture to sugar.
Mix at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 tablespoon milk, if needed.

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: Simmer	chicken
livers
in water to make 2 cups broth. When livers are done, chop fine.
In a deep skillet brown beef in
oil, bell
peppers, celery, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Cook until tender; add chicken broth.	Simmer 15 minutes.
Add rice to mixture and mix well.
Add black pepper and onions.
Cover tightly and keep heated 30 minutes.

title: coffee punch(serves 40 to 50)
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Add creamer.
Mix really well, then add milk.
Mix well.
Pour mixture of vanilla ice cream and chocolate ice cream.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: peppy bean dish
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain fat.
Add tomatoes and green chilies.
Place meat mixture in 13 x 9-inch glass casserole. Evenly spread beans over meat.
Spread corn bread mixture over meat and beans as last layer.
Bake at 425°, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and shape into balls.
Place in baking dish.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Grease pan (13 x 9-inch).
Pour in batter and cook at 350° for about 20 minutes.
While cake is hot, slice, then ice.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown bacon and onion in frying pan.
Mix flour with drippings.
Add seasoning and liquid.
Add sliced boiled eggs and sliced boiled potatoes.
Continue cooking until hot through.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and add eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add baking powder and salt to dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and cocoa (I sift the cocoa before putting in cake).
Cook in greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes in tube pan.
Makes 16 or 17 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In
a large saucepan, mix all ingredients well.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Stir and then cook on low heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: lemon-sesame asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions; drain.
Combine butter and sesame seed in a small skillet; cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until sesame seed are lightly browned.
Stir in lemon juice; pour over asparagus.

title: mom's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with sugar, salt, margarine and syrup.
Add pecans. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: basting sauce for charcoal grilling or oak wood cooking
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Baste on meats such as turkey, pork, chicken, deer, etc., approximately every 15 minutes while cooking.
For best results, after meat is browned, wrap in aluminum foil and continue basting until done.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Cut Velveeta into small pieces.
Add pimientos and most of liquid.
Add enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Use potato masher to mix until smooth and creamy.
Add mayonnaise as needed.

title: beef brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and celery salt over small brisket in a Pyrex dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 8 hours at 250°.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Place pineapple in a 10 x 10 casserole dish. Dice cream cheese over top of pineapple. Mix sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice over heat until thickened. Pour over pineapple and cream cheese. Dice marshmallows over pineapple mixture and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes until bubbly.

title: lucky microwave chicken(no time to cook, so you're lucky to get dinner!)
directions: Put chicken and stewed tomatoes in a microwave casserole dish. Cover and cook on High for 10 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Combine eggs, cottage cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
In a frying pan, brown the ground beef; drain.
Add garlic and saute.
In another bowl, mix meat, spices, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook lasagne noodles as directed.
Drain and set on paper towels.
In a 10-inch casserole dish, layer the noodles, egg mixture, tomato/meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat.
Cover with plastic wrap that is vented at one corner.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Rotate, reduce to Medium-high and microwave for 10 to 14 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: potato kugel
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into French fry size.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into shallow baking pan. Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: feist corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit sorbet
directions: Prepare
fruit	by
washing,
hulling,	peeling
and/or pitting as necessary.
Puree
in
food
processor
or blender. Pour into large bowl and blend in just enough sugar to lightly sweeten.
Add lemon juice, if desired.
Chill thoroughly, then pour into 1 gallon	canister
of
ice
cream
maker.
Pack ice and salt around canister and process until mixture is frozen. Keep frozen until serving time.	Makes 10 servings.

title: best party punch
directions: Use 1 gallon size jug or wide-opening container for ease of mixing.
Mix jello and sugar and dissolve with 2 cups very hot water.
After dissolved, pour into gallon jug or gallon container. Add pineapple juice, thawed lemonade concentrate.
Add enough water to jug or container to fill, leaving 2 inches for expansion while freezing.
Freeze until slushy.
Chill or freeze the ginger ale only until it begins to slush.
Serve by combining both the punch mixture and ginger ale together.
Should be served slushy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and mix well.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with 1/2 cup crumbs.
May refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: zucchini fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Freeze some for Christmas.

title: honey mustard pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in large plastic bag.
Combine vinegar, mustard, honey and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Pour into bag.
Seal bag securely.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove tenderloins from marinade and discard marinade.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Place tenderloins on baking rack in roasting pan.
Bake for 30 minutes. Slice into thin slices.
Spread mayonnaise over cooked meat and serve on crescent rolls.

title: chili con carne with tomatoes
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onions and green pepper in large skillet until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
(Or cook uncovered about 45 minutes.)
Stir in beans; heat.
Makes 4 to 5 servings (about 1 cup each).

title: old fashioned roast turkey(or breast of turkey)
directions: Rinse turkey quickly
and
pat
dry.
Reserve
neck and giblets for gravy.
Brush
turkey
with small amount of melted butter.
Combine seasonings and
use amount needed on skin and cavity (to taste).
Add 1 to
2 cups water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
If
not
brown,
remove cover and bake for 30 more minutes at
Cover
turkey
on
platter with foil to let it absorb
juices.
It
can
then
be stuffed with herbed seasoning such
as
Pepperidge Farm stuffing mixed with celery and sauteed chopped onion.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat well with a mixer until well blended. Grease and flour bundt pan. Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add yeast and milk to dry ingredients.
Knead on a floured board.
Roll out and cut.
Allow to rise 10 minutes.
Bake at 400°.
Cut biscuits may be frozen.
Place frozen biscuits in oven and turn to 400°. Biscuits will thaw oven heats.

title: chicken glace
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save water.
Debone chicken and ground up.
Skim fat off water and saute white part of shallots in this.
Put ground up chicken back in water and add the sauteed shallots, can of soup, pimento, and vinegar.
Simmer until all water is dissolved.
Add green part of shallots, salt and pepper. Melt gelatin in hot water and pour into chicken mixture and blend well.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until gelled.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low to medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Gently mix Rice Chex.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: vassan spatzen(german water dumplings)
directions: In a saucepan, put in 2 quarts of water and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Meanwhile, mix eggs, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon
of salt in a bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Add flour.
Beat until smooth and the consistency of gum.
You may have to add more flour or water for the right consistency.
Then tilt bowl over boiling water and with a knife, cut dough into fine strips as it slowly pours out of bowl.

title: candied cucumbers
directions: Soak 7 pounds or 7 pints of cucumbers in 2 cups of lime to 8 1/2-quarts of water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Soak in cold water for 4 hours.
Simmer cucumbers in 1 cup of vinegar, 2 ounces red food coloring, 1 tablespoon alum and enough water to cover for 2 hours.
Drain and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients together; mix well.
Form into loaf.
Place in foil-lined pan; cover with foil.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes at 400°.
Remove foil.
Cover meat loaf with catsup.
Garnish with sliced onion, if you wish.
Bake 15 minutes or more at 350° or until brown.
Makes 8 servings.
Remove form pan and slice to desired thickness.

title: green bean salad(20 minutes)
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: always-moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda in a bowl.
Mix together and make a well.
In another bowl mix the oil, lemon juice, vanilla and water.
Gradually add to the first mixture. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: toasted hamburgers
directions: Spread mixture on lower half of split buns.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or broil.
Toast upper half of buns and serve as sandwiches.

title: play dough
directions: Mix. Bake at 350° (in casserole dish) for 5 to 10 minutes. Cool slightly. Color with food coloring.
Knead until smooth. Store in airtight containers.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.
Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together. Fold dry mixture alternately with cold coffee into creamed mixture.
Mix raw apples, raisins, nuts and flour together, then fold into batter.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and chill.
Boil eggs, peel, chill and chop. Chop onions and pickles.
Mix together with about 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup sour cream and 2 tablespoons mustard.
Add more or less moist ingredients to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: inch salad
directions: In a glass salad bowl, put the lettuce.
Put each layer in bowl in the order given.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill for 24 hours.
Mix just before serving.

title: roast beef italiano
directions: Roll roast in flour; brown in hot oil.
Place in heavy roaster pan.
Add all dry seasonings.
Top roast with sliced garlic bud, diced onion, green pepper, horseradish and catsup, then add 1 cup water around meat.
Cover roaster.
Place in 350° oven for 3 to 4 hours, until very tender.
Garnish with ripe olives, tomato wedges and parsley.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixed. Add buttermilk and yeast.
Work together until sticky and mixed well.
Cover bowl; put in refrigerator.
Take out what is needed; roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Put on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until desired browness.

title: hobo's
directions: Make 4 patties from ground beef.
Place in the bottom of a Pyrex pan.
Peel and slice onions, place over meat.
Peel and slice potatoes, place over onions.
Slice carrots, place over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or until meat is done. Place cheese slices over meat and melt.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine.
Stir into crumbs and press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour evenly over crumbs.
Spoon pie filling evenly over creamy layer.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly.

title: granny engle's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add salt.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Then add extract.
Mix well and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake in a long loaf pan.

title: shirley mckenzie's clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp in a kettle.
Remove and set aside for next step.
Stir onion into drippings in kettle; saute until soft. Add potatoes, salt and clam juice.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams, tomatoes, thyme and cooked bacon.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
You may use fresh clams instead of canned, but be sure to grind them and still juice the bottle of clam juice.

title: cottage cheese and cinnamon toasty(low calorie)
directions: Toast bread until browned as desired.
Spread cottage cheese on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Place in toaster oven or under broiler until topping bubbles.
Serve at once.
Yields 1 serving.

title: grandmother smith's gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch lightly greased (Pam) pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: steamed broccoli with sesame vinaigrette
directions: Sprinkle sesame seed on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Set aside.
Trim off leaves and tough lower stalks of broccoli. Wash thoroughly and separate into spears. Arrange with stalks toward center in a vegetable steamer. Steam 6 minutes (or simmer in pan 6 minutes).
Drain. Combine sesame seed, vinegar and remaining ingredients. Stir. Drizzle over broccoli.
Exchanges:
1 vegetable, 1/2 fat.
Serving Size:
1/2 cup.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix, except for the following: instead of oil and/or water, add the cherry pie filling.
Bake as directions state.
While baking the cake, make the pudding, per the instructions (this can be shaker top or cooked pudding).
When cake is completely cool, cover with pudding and refrigerate overnight (or 8 hours).
Add Cool Whip to top of cake as a frosting.
Sprinkle with cherries, chocolate sprinkles, etc.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon and onion, then add green beans and tomatoes.
Cook and serve.

title: sue's punch
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions except use ice instead of cold water.
Add pineapple juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Separate into 3 (1 gallon) containers and freeze.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in pecans into flour mixture.
Pat into pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Fold 1 cup whipped topping into cream cheese mixture. Spread over crust.
Chill.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed of electric mixer.
Spread pudding over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: grandma shuler's ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, cinnamon, ginger, ground cloves and salt.
